31 /// ParseNamespace - We know that the current token is a namespace keyword. This
32 /// may either be a top level namespace or a block-level namespace alias. If
33 /// there was an inline keyword, it has already been parsed.
34 ///
35 /// namespace-definition: [C++: namespace.def]
36 /// named-namespace-definition
37 /// unnamed-namespace-definition
38 /// nested-namespace-definition
39 ///
40 /// named-namespace-definition:
41 /// 'inline'[opt] 'namespace' attributes[opt] identifier '{'
42 /// namespace-body '}'
43 ///
44 /// unnamed-namespace-definition:
45 /// 'inline'[opt] 'namespace' attributes[opt] '{' namespace-body '}'
46 ///
47 /// nested-namespace-definition:
48 /// 'namespace' enclosing-namespace-specifier '::' 'inline'[opt]
49 /// identifier '{' namespace-body '}'
50 ///
51 /// enclosing-namespace-specifier:
52 /// identifier
53 /// enclosing-namespace-specifier '::' 'inline'[opt] identifier
54 ///
55 /// namespace-alias-definition: [C++ 7.3.2: namespace.alias]
56 /// 'namespace' identifier '=' qualified-namespace-specifier ';'
57 ///
58 Parser::DeclGroupPtrTy Parser::ParseNamespace(DeclaratorContext Context,
59  SourceLocation &DeclEnd,
60  SourceLocation InlineLoc) {
61  assert(Tok.is(tok::kw_namespace) && "Not a namespace!");
62  SourceLocation NamespaceLoc = ConsumeToken(); // eat the 'namespace'.
63  ObjCDeclContextSwitch ObjCDC(*this);
64 
65  if (Tok.is(tok::code_completion)) {
66  cutOffParsing();
67  Actions.CodeCompleteNamespaceDecl(getCurScope());
68  return nullptr;
69  }
70 
71  SourceLocation IdentLoc;
72  IdentifierInfo *Ident = nullptr;
73  InnerNamespaceInfoList ExtraNSs;
74  SourceLocation FirstNestedInlineLoc;
75 
76  ParsedAttributes attrs(AttrFactory);
77 
78  auto ReadAttributes = [&] {
79  bool MoreToParse;
80  do {
81  MoreToParse = false;
82  if (Tok.is(tok::kw___attribute)) {
83  ParseGNUAttributes(attrs);
84  MoreToParse = true;
85  }
86  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 && isCXX11AttributeSpecifier()) {
87  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17
88  ? diag::warn_cxx14_compat_ns_enum_attribute
89  : diag::ext_ns_enum_attribute)
90  << 0 /*namespace*/;
91  ParseCXX11Attributes(attrs);
92  MoreToParse = true;
93  }
94  } while (MoreToParse);
95  };
96 
97  ReadAttributes();
98 
99  if (Tok.is(tok::identifier)) {
100  Ident = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
101  IdentLoc = ConsumeToken(); // eat the identifier.
102  while (Tok.is(tok::coloncolon) &&
103  (NextToken().is(tok::identifier) ||
104  (NextToken().is(tok::kw_inline) &&
105  GetLookAheadToken(2).is(tok::identifier)))) {
106 
107  InnerNamespaceInfo Info;
108  Info.NamespaceLoc = ConsumeToken();
109 
110  if (Tok.is(tok::kw_inline)) {
111  Info.InlineLoc = ConsumeToken();
112  if (FirstNestedInlineLoc.isInvalid())
113  FirstNestedInlineLoc = Info.InlineLoc;
114  }
115 
116  Info.Ident = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
117  Info.IdentLoc = ConsumeToken();
118 
119  ExtraNSs.push_back(Info);
120  }
121  }
122 
123  ReadAttributes();
124 
125  SourceLocation attrLoc = attrs.Range.getBegin();
126 
127  // A nested namespace definition cannot have attributes.
128  if (!ExtraNSs.empty() && attrLoc.isValid())
129  Diag(attrLoc, diag::err_unexpected_nested_namespace_attribute);
130 
131  if (Tok.is(tok::equal)) {
132  if (!Ident) {
133  Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected) << tok::identifier;
134  // Skip to end of the definition and eat the ';'.
135  SkipUntil(tok::semi);
136  return nullptr;
137  }
138  if (attrLoc.isValid())
139  Diag(attrLoc, diag::err_unexpected_namespace_attributes_alias);
140  if (InlineLoc.isValid())
141  Diag(InlineLoc, diag::err_inline_namespace_alias)
142  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(InlineLoc);
143  Decl *NSAlias = ParseNamespaceAlias(NamespaceLoc, IdentLoc, Ident, DeclEnd);
144  return Actions.ConvertDeclToDeclGroup(NSAlias);
145  }
146 
147  BalancedDelimiterTracker T(*this, tok::l_brace);
148  if (T.consumeOpen()) {
149  if (Ident)
150  Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected) << tok::l_brace;
151  else
152  Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected_either) << tok::identifier << tok::l_brace;
153  return nullptr;
154  }
155 
156  if (getCurScope()->isClassScope() || getCurScope()->isTemplateParamScope() ||
157  getCurScope()->isInObjcMethodScope() || getCurScope()->getBlockParent() ||
158  getCurScope()->getFnParent()) {
159  Diag(T.getOpenLocation(), diag::err_namespace_nonnamespace_scope);
160  SkipUntil(tok::r_brace);
161  return nullptr;
162  }
163 
164  if (ExtraNSs.empty()) {
165  // Normal namespace definition, not a nested-namespace-definition.
166  } else if (InlineLoc.isValid()) {
167  Diag(InlineLoc, diag::err_inline_nested_namespace_definition);
168  } else if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20) {
169  Diag(ExtraNSs[0].NamespaceLoc,
170  diag::warn_cxx14_compat_nested_namespace_definition);
171  if (FirstNestedInlineLoc.isValid())
172  Diag(FirstNestedInlineLoc,
173  diag::warn_cxx17_compat_inline_nested_namespace_definition);
174  } else if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17) {
175  Diag(ExtraNSs[0].NamespaceLoc,
176  diag::warn_cxx14_compat_nested_namespace_definition);
177  if (FirstNestedInlineLoc.isValid())
178  Diag(FirstNestedInlineLoc, diag::ext_inline_nested_namespace_definition);
179  } else {
180  TentativeParsingAction TPA(*this);
181  SkipUntil(tok::r_brace, StopBeforeMatch);
182  Token rBraceToken = Tok;
183  TPA.Revert();
184 
185  if (!rBraceToken.is(tok::r_brace)) {
186  Diag(ExtraNSs[0].NamespaceLoc, diag::ext_nested_namespace_definition)
187  << SourceRange(ExtraNSs.front().NamespaceLoc,
188  ExtraNSs.back().IdentLoc);
189  } else {
190  std::string NamespaceFix;
191  for (const auto &ExtraNS : ExtraNSs) {
192  NamespaceFix += " { ";
193  if (ExtraNS.InlineLoc.isValid())
194  NamespaceFix += "inline ";
195  NamespaceFix += "namespace ";
196  NamespaceFix += ExtraNS.Ident->getName();
197  }
198 
199  std::string RBraces;
200  for (unsigned i = 0, e = ExtraNSs.size(); i != e; ++i)
201  RBraces += "} ";
202 
203  Diag(ExtraNSs[0].NamespaceLoc, diag::ext_nested_namespace_definition)
204  << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(
205  SourceRange(ExtraNSs.front().NamespaceLoc,
206  ExtraNSs.back().IdentLoc),
207  NamespaceFix)
208  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(rBraceToken.getLocation(), RBraces);
209  }
210 
211  // Warn about nested inline namespaces.
212  if (FirstNestedInlineLoc.isValid())
213  Diag(FirstNestedInlineLoc, diag::ext_inline_nested_namespace_definition);
214  }
215 
216  // If we're still good, complain about inline namespaces in non-C++0x now.
217  if (InlineLoc.isValid())
218  Diag(InlineLoc, getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 ?
219  diag::warn_cxx98_compat_inline_namespace : diag::ext_inline_namespace);
220 
221  // Enter a scope for the namespace.
222  ParseScope NamespaceScope(this, Scope::DeclScope);
223 
224  UsingDirectiveDecl *ImplicitUsingDirectiveDecl = nullptr;
225  Decl *NamespcDecl = Actions.ActOnStartNamespaceDef(
226  getCurScope(), InlineLoc, NamespaceLoc, IdentLoc, Ident,
227  T.getOpenLocation(), attrs, ImplicitUsingDirectiveDecl);
228 
229  PrettyDeclStackTraceEntry CrashInfo(Actions.Context, NamespcDecl,
230  NamespaceLoc, "parsing namespace");
231 
232  // Parse the contents of the namespace. This includes parsing recovery on
233  // any improperly nested namespaces.
234  ParseInnerNamespace(ExtraNSs, 0, InlineLoc, attrs, T);
235 
236  // Leave the namespace scope.
237  NamespaceScope.Exit();
238 
239  DeclEnd = T.getCloseLocation();
240  Actions.ActOnFinishNamespaceDef(NamespcDecl, DeclEnd);
241 
242  return Actions.ConvertDeclToDeclGroup(NamespcDecl,
243  ImplicitUsingDirectiveDecl);
244 }

246 /// ParseInnerNamespace - Parse the contents of a namespace.
247 void Parser::ParseInnerNamespace(const InnerNamespaceInfoList &InnerNSs,
248  unsigned int index, SourceLocation &InlineLoc,
249  ParsedAttributes &attrs,
250  BalancedDelimiterTracker &Tracker) {
251  if (index == InnerNSs.size()) {
252  while (!tryParseMisplacedModuleImport() && Tok.isNot(tok::r_brace) &&
253  Tok.isNot(tok::eof)) {
254  ParsedAttributes Attrs(AttrFactory);
255  MaybeParseCXX11Attributes(Attrs);
256  ParseExternalDeclaration(Attrs);
257  }
258 
259  // The caller is what called check -- we are simply calling
260  // the close for it.
261  Tracker.consumeClose();
262 
263  return;
264  }
265 
266  // Handle a nested namespace definition.
267  // FIXME: Preserve the source information through to the AST rather than
268  // desugaring it here.
269  ParseScope NamespaceScope(this, Scope::DeclScope);
270  UsingDirectiveDecl *ImplicitUsingDirectiveDecl = nullptr;
271  Decl *NamespcDecl = Actions.ActOnStartNamespaceDef(
272  getCurScope(), InnerNSs[index].InlineLoc, InnerNSs[index].NamespaceLoc,
273  InnerNSs[index].IdentLoc, InnerNSs[index].Ident,
274  Tracker.getOpenLocation(), attrs, ImplicitUsingDirectiveDecl);
275  assert(!ImplicitUsingDirectiveDecl &&
276  "nested namespace definition cannot define anonymous namespace");
277 
278  ParseInnerNamespace(InnerNSs, ++index, InlineLoc, attrs, Tracker);
279 
280  NamespaceScope.Exit();
281  Actions.ActOnFinishNamespaceDef(NamespcDecl, Tracker.getCloseLocation());
282 }

284 /// ParseNamespaceAlias - Parse the part after the '=' in a namespace
285 /// alias definition.
286 ///
287 Decl *Parser::ParseNamespaceAlias(SourceLocation NamespaceLoc,
288  SourceLocation AliasLoc,
289  IdentifierInfo *Alias,
290  SourceLocation &DeclEnd) {
291  assert(Tok.is(tok::equal) && "Not equal token");
292 
293  ConsumeToken(); // eat the '='.
294 
295  if (Tok.is(tok::code_completion)) {
296  cutOffParsing();
297  Actions.CodeCompleteNamespaceAliasDecl(getCurScope());
298  return nullptr;
299  }
300 
301  CXXScopeSpec SS;
302  // Parse (optional) nested-name-specifier.
303  ParseOptionalCXXScopeSpecifier(SS, /*ObjectType=*/nullptr,
304  /*ObjectHasErrors=*/false,
305  /*EnteringContext=*/false,
306  /*MayBePseudoDestructor=*/nullptr,
307  /*IsTypename=*/false,
308  /*LastII=*/nullptr,
309  /*OnlyNamespace=*/true);
310 
311  if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) {
312  Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected_namespace_name);
313  // Skip to end of the definition and eat the ';'.
314  SkipUntil(tok::semi);
315  return nullptr;
316  }
317 
318  if (SS.isInvalid()) {
319  // Diagnostics have been emitted in ParseOptionalCXXScopeSpecifier.
320  // Skip to end of the definition and eat the ';'.
321  SkipUntil(tok::semi);
322  return nullptr;
323  }
324 
325  // Parse identifier.
326  IdentifierInfo *Ident = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
327  SourceLocation IdentLoc = ConsumeToken();
328 
329  // Eat the ';'.
330  DeclEnd = Tok.getLocation();
331  if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::semi, diag::err_expected_semi_after_namespace_name))
332  SkipUntil(tok::semi);
333 
334  return Actions.ActOnNamespaceAliasDef(getCurScope(), NamespaceLoc, AliasLoc,
335  Alias, SS, IdentLoc, Ident);
336 }

338 /// ParseLinkage - We know that the current token is a string_literal
339 /// and just before that, that extern was seen.
340 ///
341 /// linkage-specification: [C++ 7.5p2: dcl.link]
342 /// 'extern' string-literal '{' declaration-seq[opt] '}'
343 /// 'extern' string-literal declaration
344 ///
345 Decl *Parser::ParseLinkage(ParsingDeclSpec &DS, DeclaratorContext Context) {
346  assert(isTokenStringLiteral() && "Not a string literal!");
347  ExprResult Lang = ParseStringLiteralExpression(false);
348 
349  ParseScope LinkageScope(this, Scope::DeclScope);
350  Decl *LinkageSpec =
351  Lang.isInvalid()
352  ? nullptr
353  : Actions.ActOnStartLinkageSpecification(
354  getCurScope(), DS.getSourceRange().getBegin(), Lang.get(),
355  Tok.is(tok::l_brace) ? Tok.getLocation() : SourceLocation());
356 
357  ParsedAttributes attrs(AttrFactory);
358  MaybeParseCXX11Attributes(attrs);
359 
360  if (Tok.isNot(tok::l_brace)) {
361  // Reset the source range in DS, as the leading "extern"
362  // does not really belong to the inner declaration ...
363  DS.SetRangeStart(SourceLocation());
364  DS.SetRangeEnd(SourceLocation());
365  // ... but anyway remember that such an "extern" was seen.
366  DS.setExternInLinkageSpec(true);
367  ParseExternalDeclaration(attrs, &DS);
368  return LinkageSpec ? Actions.ActOnFinishLinkageSpecification(
369  getCurScope(), LinkageSpec, SourceLocation())
370  : nullptr;
371  }
372 
373  DS.abort();
374 
375  ProhibitAttributes(attrs);
376 
377  BalancedDelimiterTracker T(*this, tok::l_brace);
378  T.consumeOpen();
379 
380  unsigned NestedModules = 0;
381  while (true) {
382  switch (Tok.getKind()) {
383  case tok::annot_module_begin:
384  ++NestedModules;
385  ParseTopLevelDecl();
386  continue;
387 
388  case tok::annot_module_end:
389  if (!NestedModules)
390  break;
391  --NestedModules;
392  ParseTopLevelDecl();
393  continue;
394 
395  case tok::annot_module_include:
396  ParseTopLevelDecl();
397  continue;
398 
399  case tok::eof:
400  break;
401 
402  case tok::r_brace:
403  if (!NestedModules)
404  break;
405  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
406  default:
407  ParsedAttributes Attrs(AttrFactory);
408  MaybeParseCXX11Attributes(Attrs);
409  ParseExternalDeclaration(Attrs);
410  continue;
411  }
412 
413  break;
414  }
415 
416  T.consumeClose();
417  return LinkageSpec ? Actions.ActOnFinishLinkageSpecification(
418  getCurScope(), LinkageSpec, T.getCloseLocation())
419  : nullptr;
420 }

422 /// Parse a C++ Modules TS export-declaration.
423 ///
424 /// export-declaration:
425 /// 'export' declaration
426 /// 'export' '{' declaration-seq[opt] '}'
427 ///
428 Decl *Parser::ParseExportDeclaration() {
429  assert(Tok.is(tok::kw_export));
430  SourceLocation ExportLoc = ConsumeToken();
431 
432  ParseScope ExportScope(this, Scope::DeclScope);
433  Decl *ExportDecl = Actions.ActOnStartExportDecl(
434  getCurScope(), ExportLoc,
435  Tok.is(tok::l_brace) ? Tok.getLocation() : SourceLocation());
436 
437  if (Tok.isNot(tok::l_brace)) {
438  // FIXME: Factor out a ParseExternalDeclarationWithAttrs.
439  ParsedAttributes Attrs(AttrFactory);
440  MaybeParseCXX11Attributes(Attrs);
441  MaybeParseMicrosoftAttributes(Attrs);
442  ParseExternalDeclaration(Attrs);
443  return Actions.ActOnFinishExportDecl(getCurScope(), ExportDecl,
444  SourceLocation());
445  }
446 
447  BalancedDelimiterTracker T(*this, tok::l_brace);
448  T.consumeOpen();
449 
450  // The Modules TS draft says "An export-declaration shall declare at least one
451  // entity", but the intent is that it shall contain at least one declaration.
452  if (Tok.is(tok::r_brace) && getLangOpts().ModulesTS) {
453  Diag(ExportLoc, diag::err_export_empty)
454  << SourceRange(ExportLoc, Tok.getLocation());
455  }
456 
457  while (!tryParseMisplacedModuleImport() && Tok.isNot(tok::r_brace) &&
458  Tok.isNot(tok::eof)) {
459  ParsedAttributes Attrs(AttrFactory);
460  MaybeParseCXX11Attributes(Attrs);
461  MaybeParseMicrosoftAttributes(Attrs);
462  ParseExternalDeclaration(Attrs);
463  }
464 
465  T.consumeClose();
466  return Actions.ActOnFinishExportDecl(getCurScope(), ExportDecl,
467  T.getCloseLocation());
468 }

470 /// ParseUsingDirectiveOrDeclaration - Parse C++ using using-declaration or
471 /// using-directive. Assumes that current token is 'using'.
472 Parser::DeclGroupPtrTy Parser::ParseUsingDirectiveOrDeclaration(
473  DeclaratorContext Context, const ParsedTemplateInfo &TemplateInfo,
474  SourceLocation &DeclEnd, ParsedAttributes &Attrs) {
475  assert(Tok.is(tok::kw_using) && "Not using token");
476  ObjCDeclContextSwitch ObjCDC(*this);
477 
478  // Eat 'using'.
479  SourceLocation UsingLoc = ConsumeToken();
480 
481  if (Tok.is(tok::code_completion)) {
482  cutOffParsing();
483  Actions.CodeCompleteUsing(getCurScope());
484  return nullptr;
485  }
486 
487  // Consume unexpected 'template' keywords.
488  while (Tok.is(tok::kw_template)) {
489  SourceLocation TemplateLoc = ConsumeToken();
490  Diag(TemplateLoc, diag::err_unexpected_template_after_using)
491  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(TemplateLoc);
492  }
493 
494  // 'using namespace' means this is a using-directive.
495  if (Tok.is(tok::kw_namespace)) {
496  // Template parameters are always an error here.
497  if (TemplateInfo.Kind) {
498  SourceRange R = TemplateInfo.getSourceRange();
499  Diag(UsingLoc, diag::err_templated_using_directive_declaration)
500  << 0 /* directive */ << R << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(R);
501  }
502 
503  Decl *UsingDir = ParseUsingDirective(Context, UsingLoc, DeclEnd, Attrs);
504  return Actions.ConvertDeclToDeclGroup(UsingDir);
505  }
506 
507  // Otherwise, it must be a using-declaration or an alias-declaration.
508  return ParseUsingDeclaration(Context, TemplateInfo, UsingLoc, DeclEnd, Attrs,
509  AS_none);
510 }

512 /// ParseUsingDirective - Parse C++ using-directive, assumes
513 /// that current token is 'namespace' and 'using' was already parsed.
514 ///
515 /// using-directive: [C++ 7.3.p4: namespace.udir]
516 /// 'using' 'namespace' ::[opt] nested-name-specifier[opt]
517 /// namespace-name ;
518 /// [GNU] using-directive:
519 /// 'using' 'namespace' ::[opt] nested-name-specifier[opt]
520 /// namespace-name attributes[opt] ;
521 ///
522 Decl *Parser::ParseUsingDirective(DeclaratorContext Context,
523  SourceLocation UsingLoc,
524  SourceLocation &DeclEnd,
525  ParsedAttributes &attrs) {
526  assert(Tok.is(tok::kw_namespace) && "Not 'namespace' token");
527 
528  // Eat 'namespace'.
529  SourceLocation NamespcLoc = ConsumeToken();
530 
531  if (Tok.is(tok::code_completion)) {
532  cutOffParsing();
533  Actions.CodeCompleteUsingDirective(getCurScope());
534  return nullptr;
535  }
536 
537  CXXScopeSpec SS;
538  // Parse (optional) nested-name-specifier.
539  ParseOptionalCXXScopeSpecifier(SS, /*ObjectType=*/nullptr,
540  /*ObjectHasErrors=*/false,
541  /*EnteringContext=*/false,
542  /*MayBePseudoDestructor=*/nullptr,
543  /*IsTypename=*/false,
544  /*LastII=*/nullptr,
545  /*OnlyNamespace=*/true);
546 
547  IdentifierInfo *NamespcName = nullptr;
548  SourceLocation IdentLoc = SourceLocation();
549 
550  // Parse namespace-name.
551  if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) {
552  Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected_namespace_name);
553  // If there was invalid namespace name, skip to end of decl, and eat ';'.
554  SkipUntil(tok::semi);
555  // FIXME: Are there cases, when we would like to call ActOnUsingDirective?
556  return nullptr;
557  }
558 
559  if (SS.isInvalid()) {
560  // Diagnostics have been emitted in ParseOptionalCXXScopeSpecifier.
561  // Skip to end of the definition and eat the ';'.
562  SkipUntil(tok::semi);
563  return nullptr;
564  }
565 
566  // Parse identifier.
567  NamespcName = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
568  IdentLoc = ConsumeToken();
569 
570  // Parse (optional) attributes (most likely GNU strong-using extension).
571  bool GNUAttr = false;
572  if (Tok.is(tok::kw___attribute)) {
573  GNUAttr = true;
574  ParseGNUAttributes(attrs);
575  }
576 
577  // Eat ';'.
578  DeclEnd = Tok.getLocation();
579  if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::semi,
580  GNUAttr ? diag::err_expected_semi_after_attribute_list
581  : diag::err_expected_semi_after_namespace_name))
582  SkipUntil(tok::semi);
583 
584  return Actions.ActOnUsingDirective(getCurScope(), UsingLoc, NamespcLoc, SS,
585  IdentLoc, NamespcName, attrs);
586 }

588 /// Parse a using-declarator (or the identifier in a C++11 alias-declaration).
589 ///
590 /// using-declarator:
591 /// 'typename'[opt] nested-name-specifier unqualified-id
592 ///
593 bool Parser::ParseUsingDeclarator(DeclaratorContext Context,
594  UsingDeclarator &D) {
595  D.clear();
596 
597  // Ignore optional 'typename'.
598  // FIXME: This is wrong; we should parse this as a typename-specifier.
599  TryConsumeToken(tok::kw_typename, D.TypenameLoc);
600 
601  if (Tok.is(tok::kw___super)) {
602  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_super_in_using_declaration);
603  return true;
604  }
605 
606  // Parse nested-name-specifier.
607  IdentifierInfo *LastII = nullptr;
608  if (ParseOptionalCXXScopeSpecifier(D.SS, /*ObjectType=*/nullptr,
609  /*ObjectHasErrors=*/false,
610  /*EnteringContext=*/false,
611  /*MayBePseudoDtor=*/nullptr,
612  /*IsTypename=*/false,
613  /*LastII=*/&LastII,
614  /*OnlyNamespace=*/false,
615  /*InUsingDeclaration=*/true))
616 
617  return true;
618  if (D.SS.isInvalid())
619  return true;
620 
621  // Parse the unqualified-id. We allow parsing of both constructor and
622  // destructor names and allow the action module to diagnose any semantic
623  // errors.
624  //
625  // C++11 [class.qual]p2:
626  // [...] in a using-declaration that is a member-declaration, if the name
627  // specified after the nested-name-specifier is the same as the identifier
628  // or the simple-template-id's template-name in the last component of the
629  // nested-name-specifier, the name is [...] considered to name the
630  // constructor.
631  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 && Context == DeclaratorContext::Member &&
632  Tok.is(tok::identifier) &&
633  (NextToken().is(tok::semi) || NextToken().is(tok::comma) ||
634  NextToken().is(tok::ellipsis) || NextToken().is(tok::l_square) ||
635  NextToken().is(tok::kw___attribute)) &&
636  D.SS.isNotEmpty() && LastII == Tok.getIdentifierInfo() &&
637  !D.SS.getScopeRep()->getAsNamespace() &&
638  !D.SS.getScopeRep()->getAsNamespaceAlias()) {
639  SourceLocation IdLoc = ConsumeToken();
640  ParsedType Type =
641  Actions.getInheritingConstructorName(D.SS, IdLoc, *LastII);
642  D.Name.setConstructorName(Type, IdLoc, IdLoc);
643  } else {
644  if (ParseUnqualifiedId(
645  D.SS, /*ObjectType=*/nullptr,
646  /*ObjectHadErrors=*/false, /*EnteringContext=*/false,
647  /*AllowDestructorName=*/true,
648  /*AllowConstructorName=*/
649  !(Tok.is(tok::identifier) && NextToken().is(tok::equal)),
650  /*AllowDeductionGuide=*/false, nullptr, D.Name))
651  return true;
652  }
653 
654  if (TryConsumeToken(tok::ellipsis, D.EllipsisLoc))
655  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17 ?
656  diag::warn_cxx17_compat_using_declaration_pack :
657  diag::ext_using_declaration_pack);
658 
659  return false;
660 }
661 
662 /// ParseUsingDeclaration - Parse C++ using-declaration or alias-declaration.
663 /// Assumes that 'using' was already seen.
664 ///
665 /// using-declaration: [C++ 7.3.p3: namespace.udecl]
666 /// 'using' using-declarator-list[opt] ;
667 ///
668 /// using-declarator-list: [C++1z]
669 /// using-declarator '...'[opt]
670 /// using-declarator-list ',' using-declarator '...'[opt]
671 ///
672 /// using-declarator-list: [C++98-14]
673 /// using-declarator
674 ///
675 /// alias-declaration: C++11 [dcl.dcl]p1
676 /// 'using' identifier attribute-specifier-seq[opt] = type-id ;
677 ///
678 /// using-enum-declaration: [C++20, dcl.enum]
679 /// 'using' elaborated-enum-specifier ;
680 ///
681 /// elaborated-enum-specifier:
682 /// 'enum' nested-name-specifier[opt] identifier
683 Parser::DeclGroupPtrTy Parser::ParseUsingDeclaration(
684  DeclaratorContext Context, const ParsedTemplateInfo &TemplateInfo,
685  SourceLocation UsingLoc, SourceLocation &DeclEnd,
686  ParsedAttributes &PrefixAttrs, AccessSpecifier AS) {
687  SourceLocation UELoc;
688  bool InInitStatement = Context == DeclaratorContext::SelectionInit ||
689  Context == DeclaratorContext::ForInit;
690 
691  if (TryConsumeToken(tok::kw_enum, UELoc) && !InInitStatement) {
692  // C++20 using-enum
693  Diag(UELoc, getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20
694  ? diag::warn_cxx17_compat_using_enum_declaration
695  : diag::ext_using_enum_declaration);
696 
697  DiagnoseCXX11AttributeExtension(PrefixAttrs);
698 
699  DeclSpec DS(AttrFactory);
700  ParseEnumSpecifier(UELoc, DS, TemplateInfo, AS,
701  // DSC_trailing has the semantics we desire
702  DeclSpecContext::DSC_trailing);
703 
704  if (TemplateInfo.Kind) {
705  SourceRange R = TemplateInfo.getSourceRange();
706  Diag(UsingLoc, diag::err_templated_using_directive_declaration)
707  << 1 /* declaration */ << R << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(R);
708 
709  return nullptr;
710  }
711 
712  Decl *UED = Actions.ActOnUsingEnumDeclaration(getCurScope(), AS, UsingLoc,
713  UELoc, DS);
714  DeclEnd = Tok.getLocation();
715  if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::semi, diag::err_expected_after,
716  "using-enum declaration"))
717  SkipUntil(tok::semi);
718 
719  return Actions.ConvertDeclToDeclGroup(UED);
720  }
721 
722  // Check for misplaced attributes before the identifier in an
723  // alias-declaration.
724  ParsedAttributes MisplacedAttrs(AttrFactory);
725  MaybeParseCXX11Attributes(MisplacedAttrs);
726 
727  if (InInitStatement && Tok.isNot(tok::identifier))
728  return nullptr;
729 
730  UsingDeclarator D;
731  bool InvalidDeclarator = ParseUsingDeclarator(Context, D);
732 
733  ParsedAttributes Attrs(AttrFactory);
734  MaybeParseAttributes(PAKM_GNU | PAKM_CXX11, Attrs);
735 
736  // If we had any misplaced attributes from earlier, this is where they
737  // should have been written.
738  if (MisplacedAttrs.Range.isValid()) {
739  Diag(MisplacedAttrs.Range.getBegin(), diag::err_attributes_not_allowed)
740  << FixItHint::CreateInsertionFromRange(
741  Tok.getLocation(),
742  CharSourceRange::getTokenRange(MisplacedAttrs.Range))
743  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(MisplacedAttrs.Range);
744  Attrs.takeAllFrom(MisplacedAttrs);
745  }
746 
747  // Maybe this is an alias-declaration.
748  if (Tok.is(tok::equal) || InInitStatement) {
749  if (InvalidDeclarator) {
750  SkipUntil(tok::semi);
751  return nullptr;
752  }
753 
754  ProhibitAttributes(PrefixAttrs);
755 
756  Decl *DeclFromDeclSpec = nullptr;
757  Decl *AD = ParseAliasDeclarationAfterDeclarator(
758  TemplateInfo, UsingLoc, D, DeclEnd, AS, Attrs, &DeclFromDeclSpec);
759  return Actions.ConvertDeclToDeclGroup(AD, DeclFromDeclSpec);
760  }
761 
762  DiagnoseCXX11AttributeExtension(PrefixAttrs);
763 
764  // Diagnose an attempt to declare a templated using-declaration.
765  // In C++11, alias-declarations can be templates:
766  // template <...> using id = type;
767  if (TemplateInfo.Kind) {
768  SourceRange R = TemplateInfo.getSourceRange();
769  Diag(UsingLoc, diag::err_templated_using_directive_declaration)
770  << 1 /* declaration */ << R << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(R);
771 
772  // Unfortunately, we have to bail out instead of recovering by
773  // ignoring the parameters, just in case the nested name specifier
774  // depends on the parameters.
775  return nullptr;
776  }
777 
778  SmallVector<Decl *, 8> DeclsInGroup;
779  while (true) {
780  // Parse (optional) attributes.
781  MaybeParseAttributes(PAKM_GNU | PAKM_CXX11, Attrs);
782  DiagnoseCXX11AttributeExtension(Attrs);
783  Attrs.addAll(PrefixAttrs.begin(), PrefixAttrs.end());
784 
785  if (InvalidDeclarator)
786  SkipUntil(tok::comma, tok::semi, StopBeforeMatch);
787  else {
788  // "typename" keyword is allowed for identifiers only,
789  // because it may be a type definition.
790  if (D.TypenameLoc.isValid() &&
791  D.Name.getKind() != UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_Identifier) {
792  Diag(D.Name.getSourceRange().getBegin(),
793  diag::err_typename_identifiers_only)
794  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(SourceRange(D.TypenameLoc));
795  // Proceed parsing, but discard the typename keyword.
796  D.TypenameLoc = SourceLocation();
797  }
798 
799  Decl *UD = Actions.ActOnUsingDeclaration(getCurScope(), AS, UsingLoc,
800  D.TypenameLoc, D.SS, D.Name,
801  D.EllipsisLoc, Attrs);
802  if (UD)
803  DeclsInGroup.push_back(UD);
804  }
805 
806  if (!TryConsumeToken(tok::comma))
807  break;
808 
809  // Parse another using-declarator.
810  Attrs.clear();
811  InvalidDeclarator = ParseUsingDeclarator(Context, D);
812  }
813 
814  if (DeclsInGroup.size() > 1)
815  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17 ?
816  diag::warn_cxx17_compat_multi_using_declaration :
817  diag::ext_multi_using_declaration);
818 
819  // Eat ';'.
820  DeclEnd = Tok.getLocation();
821  if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::semi, diag::err_expected_after,
822  !Attrs.empty() ? "attributes list"
823  : UELoc.isValid() ? "using-enum declaration"
824  : "using declaration"))
825  SkipUntil(tok::semi);
826 
827  return Actions.BuildDeclaratorGroup(DeclsInGroup);
828 }
829 
830 Decl *Parser::ParseAliasDeclarationAfterDeclarator(
831  const ParsedTemplateInfo &TemplateInfo, SourceLocation UsingLoc,
832  UsingDeclarator &D, SourceLocation &DeclEnd, AccessSpecifier AS,
833  ParsedAttributes &Attrs, Decl **OwnedType) {
834  if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::equal)) {
835  SkipUntil(tok::semi);
836  return nullptr;
837  }
838 
839  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 ?
840  diag::warn_cxx98_compat_alias_declaration :
841  diag::ext_alias_declaration);
842 
843  // Type alias templates cannot be specialized.
844  int SpecKind = -1;
845  if (TemplateInfo.Kind == ParsedTemplateInfo::Template &&
846  D.Name.getKind() == UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_TemplateId)
847  SpecKind = 0;
848  if (TemplateInfo.Kind == ParsedTemplateInfo::ExplicitSpecialization)
849  SpecKind = 1;
850  if (TemplateInfo.Kind == ParsedTemplateInfo::ExplicitInstantiation)
851  SpecKind = 2;
852  if (SpecKind != -1) {
853  SourceRange Range;
854  if (SpecKind == 0)
855  Range = SourceRange(D.Name.TemplateId->LAngleLoc,
856  D.Name.TemplateId->RAngleLoc);
857  else
858  Range = TemplateInfo.getSourceRange();
859  Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::err_alias_declaration_specialization)
860  << SpecKind << Range;
861  SkipUntil(tok::semi);
862  return nullptr;
863  }
864 
865  // Name must be an identifier.
866  if (D.Name.getKind() != UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_Identifier) {
867  Diag(D.Name.StartLocation, diag::err_alias_declaration_not_identifier);
868  // No removal fixit: can't recover from this.
869  SkipUntil(tok::semi);
870  return nullptr;
871  } else if (D.TypenameLoc.isValid())
872  Diag(D.TypenameLoc, diag::err_alias_declaration_not_identifier)
873  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(SourceRange(
874  D.TypenameLoc,
875  D.SS.isNotEmpty() ? D.SS.getEndLoc() : D.TypenameLoc));
876  else if (D.SS.isNotEmpty())
877  Diag(D.SS.getBeginLoc(), diag::err_alias_declaration_not_identifier)
878  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(D.SS.getRange());
879  if (D.EllipsisLoc.isValid())
880  Diag(D.EllipsisLoc, diag::err_alias_declaration_pack_expansion)
881  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(SourceRange(D.EllipsisLoc));
882 
883  Decl *DeclFromDeclSpec = nullptr;
884  TypeResult TypeAlias =
885  ParseTypeName(nullptr,
886  TemplateInfo.Kind ? DeclaratorContext::AliasTemplate
887  : DeclaratorContext::AliasDecl,
888  AS, &DeclFromDeclSpec, &Attrs);
889  if (OwnedType)
890  *OwnedType = DeclFromDeclSpec;
891 
892  // Eat ';'.
893  DeclEnd = Tok.getLocation();
894  if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::semi, diag::err_expected_after,
895  !Attrs.empty() ? "attributes list"
896  : "alias declaration"))
897  SkipUntil(tok::semi);
898 
899  TemplateParameterLists *TemplateParams = TemplateInfo.TemplateParams;
900  MultiTemplateParamsArg TemplateParamsArg(
901  TemplateParams ? TemplateParams->data() : nullptr,
902  TemplateParams ? TemplateParams->size() : 0);
903  return Actions.ActOnAliasDeclaration(getCurScope(), AS, TemplateParamsArg,
904  UsingLoc, D.Name, Attrs, TypeAlias,
905  DeclFromDeclSpec);
906 }

908 static FixItHint getStaticAssertNoMessageFixIt(const Expr *AssertExpr,
909  SourceLocation EndExprLoc) {
910  if (const auto *BO = dyn_cast_or_null<BinaryOperator>(AssertExpr)) {
911  if (BO->getOpcode() == BO_LAnd &&
912  isa<StringLiteral>(BO->getRHS()->IgnoreImpCasts()))
913  return FixItHint::CreateReplacement(BO->getOperatorLoc(), ",");
914  }
915  return FixItHint::CreateInsertion(EndExprLoc, ", \"\"");
916 }

918 /// ParseStaticAssertDeclaration - Parse C++0x or C11 static_assert-declaration.
919 ///
920 /// [C++0x] static_assert-declaration:
921 /// static_assert ( constant-expression , string-literal ) ;
922 ///
923 /// [C11] static_assert-declaration:
924 /// _Static_assert ( constant-expression , string-literal ) ;
925 ///
926 Decl *Parser::ParseStaticAssertDeclaration(SourceLocation &DeclEnd){
927  assert(Tok.isOneOf(tok::kw_static_assert, tok::kw__Static_assert) &&
928  "Not a static_assert declaration");
929 
930  if (Tok.is(tok::kw__Static_assert) && !getLangOpts().C11)
931  Diag(Tok, diag::ext_c11_feature) << Tok.getName();
932  if (Tok.is(tok::kw_static_assert)) {
933  if (!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
934  Diag(Tok, diag::ext_ms_static_assert)
935  << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(Tok.getLocation(), "_Static_assert");
936  else
937  Diag(Tok, diag::warn_cxx98_compat_static_assert);
938  }
939 
940  SourceLocation StaticAssertLoc = ConsumeToken();
941 
942  BalancedDelimiterTracker T(*this, tok::l_paren);
943  if (T.consumeOpen()) {
944  Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected) << tok::l_paren;
945  SkipMalformedDecl();
946  return nullptr;
947  }
948 
949  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext ConstantEvaluated(
950  Actions, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
951  ExprResult AssertExpr(ParseConstantExpressionInExprEvalContext());
952  if (AssertExpr.isInvalid()) {
953  SkipMalformedDecl();
954  return nullptr;
955  }
956 
957  ExprResult AssertMessage;
958  if (Tok.is(tok::r_paren)) {
959  unsigned DiagVal;
960  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17)
961  DiagVal = diag::warn_cxx14_compat_static_assert_no_message;
962  else if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
963  DiagVal = diag::ext_cxx_static_assert_no_message;
964  else if (getLangOpts().C2x)
965  DiagVal = diag::warn_c17_compat_static_assert_no_message;
966  else
967  DiagVal = diag::ext_c_static_assert_no_message;
968  Diag(Tok, DiagVal) << getStaticAssertNoMessageFixIt(AssertExpr.get(),
969  Tok.getLocation());
970  } else {
971  if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::comma)) {
972  SkipUntil(tok::semi);
973  return nullptr;
974  }
975 
976  if (!isTokenStringLiteral()) {
977  Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected_string_literal)
978  << /*Source='static_assert'*/1;
979  SkipMalformedDecl();
980  return nullptr;
981  }
982 
983  AssertMessage = ParseStringLiteralExpression();
984  if (AssertMessage.isInvalid()) {
985  SkipMalformedDecl();
986  return nullptr;
987  }
988  }
989 
990  T.consumeClose();
991 
992  DeclEnd = Tok.getLocation();
993  ExpectAndConsumeSemi(diag::err_expected_semi_after_static_assert);
994 
995  return Actions.ActOnStaticAssertDeclaration(StaticAssertLoc,
996  AssertExpr.get(),
997  AssertMessage.get(),
998  T.getCloseLocation());
999 }

1001 /// ParseDecltypeSpecifier - Parse a C++11 decltype specifier.
1002 ///
1003 /// 'decltype' ( expression )
1004 /// 'decltype' ( 'auto' ) [C++1y]
1005 ///
1006 SourceLocation Parser::ParseDecltypeSpecifier(DeclSpec &DS) {
1007  assert(Tok.isOneOf(tok::kw_decltype, tok::annot_decltype)
1008  && "Not a decltype specifier");
1009 
1010  ExprResult Result;
1011  SourceLocation StartLoc = Tok.getLocation();
1012  SourceLocation EndLoc;
1013 
1014  if (Tok.is(tok::annot_decltype)) {
1015  Result = getExprAnnotation(Tok);
1016  EndLoc = Tok.getAnnotationEndLoc();
1017  // Unfortunately, we don't know the LParen source location as the annotated
1018  // token doesn't have it.
1019  DS.setTypeofParensRange(SourceRange(SourceLocation(), EndLoc));
1020  ConsumeAnnotationToken();
1021  if (Result.isInvalid()) {
1022  DS.SetTypeSpecError();
1023  return EndLoc;
1024  }
1025  } else {
1026  if (Tok.getIdentifierInfo()->isStr("decltype"))
1027  Diag(Tok, diag::warn_cxx98_compat_decltype);
1028 
1029  ConsumeToken();
1030 
1031  BalancedDelimiterTracker T(*this, tok::l_paren);
1032  if (T.expectAndConsume(diag::err_expected_lparen_after,
1033  "decltype", tok::r_paren)) {
1034  DS.SetTypeSpecError();
1035  return T.getOpenLocation() == Tok.getLocation() ?
1036  StartLoc : T.getOpenLocation();
1037  }
1038 
1039  // Check for C++1y 'decltype(auto)'.
1040  if (Tok.is(tok::kw_auto) && NextToken().is(tok::r_paren)) {
1041  // the typename-specifier in a function-style cast expression may
1042  // be 'auto' since C++2b.
1043  Diag(Tok.getLocation(),
1044  getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14
1045  ? diag::warn_cxx11_compat_decltype_auto_type_specifier
1046  : diag::ext_decltype_auto_type_specifier);
1047  ConsumeToken();
1048  } else {
1049  // Parse the expression
1050 
1051  // C++11 [dcl.type.simple]p4:
1052  // The operand of the decltype specifier is an unevaluated operand.
1053  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
1054  Actions, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated, nullptr,
1055  Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContextRecord::EK_Decltype);
1056  Result = Actions.CorrectDelayedTyposInExpr(
1057  ParseExpression(), /*InitDecl=*/nullptr,
1058  /*RecoverUncorrectedTypos=*/false,
1059  [](Expr *E) { return E->hasPlaceholderType() ? ExprError() : E; });
1060  if (Result.isInvalid()) {
1061  DS.SetTypeSpecError();
1062  if (SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi | StopBeforeMatch)) {
1063  EndLoc = ConsumeParen();
1064  } else {
1065  if (PP.isBacktrackEnabled() && Tok.is(tok::semi)) {
1066  // Backtrack to get the location of the last token before the semi.
1067  PP.RevertCachedTokens(2);
1068  ConsumeToken(); // the semi.
1069  EndLoc = ConsumeAnyToken();
1070  assert(Tok.is(tok::semi));
1071  } else {
1072  EndLoc = Tok.getLocation();
1073  }
1074  }
1075  return EndLoc;
1076  }
1077 
1078  Result = Actions.ActOnDecltypeExpression(Result.get());
1079  }
1080 
1081  // Match the ')'
1082  T.consumeClose();
1083  DS.setTypeofParensRange(T.getRange());
1084  if (T.getCloseLocation().isInvalid()) {
1085  DS.SetTypeSpecError();
1086  // FIXME: this should return the location of the last token
1087  // that was consumed (by "consumeClose()")
1088  return T.getCloseLocation();
1089  }
1090 
1091  if (Result.isInvalid()) {
1092  DS.SetTypeSpecError();
1093  return T.getCloseLocation();
1094  }
1095 
1096  EndLoc = T.getCloseLocation();
1097  }
1098  assert(!Result.isInvalid());
1099 
1100  const char *PrevSpec = nullptr;
1101  unsigned DiagID;
1102  const PrintingPolicy &Policy = Actions.getASTContext().getPrintingPolicy();
1103  // Check for duplicate type specifiers (e.g. "int decltype(a)").
1104  if (Result.get()
1105  ? DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_decltype, StartLoc, PrevSpec,
1106  DiagID, Result.get(), Policy)
1107  : DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_decltype_auto, StartLoc, PrevSpec,
1108  DiagID, Policy)) {
1109  Diag(StartLoc, DiagID) << PrevSpec;
1110  DS.SetTypeSpecError();
1111  }
1112  return EndLoc;
1113 }

1115 void Parser::AnnotateExistingDecltypeSpecifier(const DeclSpec& DS,
1116  SourceLocation StartLoc,
1117  SourceLocation EndLoc) {
1118  // make sure we have a token we can turn into an annotation token
1119  if (PP.isBacktrackEnabled()) {
1120  PP.RevertCachedTokens(1);
1121  if (DS.getTypeSpecType() == TST_error) {
1122  // We encountered an error in parsing 'decltype(...)' so lets annotate all
1123  // the tokens in the backtracking cache - that we likely had to skip over
1124  // to get to a token that allows us to resume parsing, such as a
1125  // semi-colon.
1126  EndLoc = PP.getLastCachedTokenLocation();
1127  }
1128  }
1129  else
1130  PP.EnterToken(Tok, /*IsReinject*/true);
1131 
1132  Tok.setKind(tok::annot_decltype);
1133  setExprAnnotation(Tok,
1134  DS.getTypeSpecType() == TST_decltype ? DS.getRepAsExpr() :
1135  DS.getTypeSpecType() == TST_decltype_auto ? ExprResult() :
1136  ExprError());
1137  Tok.setAnnotationEndLoc(EndLoc);
1138  Tok.setLocation(StartLoc);
1139  PP.AnnotateCachedTokens(Tok);
1140 }

1142 void Parser::ParseUnderlyingTypeSpecifier(DeclSpec &DS) {
1143  assert(Tok.is(tok::kw___underlying_type) &&
1144  "Not an underlying type specifier");
1145 
1146  SourceLocation StartLoc = ConsumeToken();
1147  BalancedDelimiterTracker T(*this, tok::l_paren);
1148  if (T.expectAndConsume(diag::err_expected_lparen_after,
1149  "__underlying_type", tok::r_paren)) {
1150  return;
1151  }
1152

1154  if (Result.isInvalid()) {
1155  SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
1156  return;
1157  }
1158 
1159  // Match the ')'
1160  T.consumeClose();
1161  if (T.getCloseLocation().isInvalid())
1162  return;

1164  const char *PrevSpec = nullptr;

1166  if (DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_underlyingType, StartLoc, PrevSpec,
1167  DiagID, Result.get(),

1169  Diag(StartLoc, DiagID) << PrevSpec;
1170  DS.setTypeofParensRange(T.getRange());
1171 }

1173 /// ParseBaseTypeSpecifier - Parse a C++ base-type-specifier which is either a
1174 /// class name or decltype-specifier. Note that we only check that the result
1175 /// names a type; semantic analysis will need to verify that the type names a
1176 /// class. The result is either a type or null, depending on whether a type
1177 /// name was found.
1178 ///
1179 /// base-type-specifier: [C++11 class.derived]
1180 /// class-or-decltype
1181 /// class-or-decltype: [C++11 class.derived]
1182 /// nested-name-specifier[opt] class-name
1183 /// decltype-specifier
1184 /// class-name: [C++ class.name]
1185 /// identifier
1186 /// simple-template-id
1187 ///
1188 /// In C++98, instead of base-type-specifier, we have:
1189 ///
1190 /// ::[opt] nested-name-specifier[opt] class-name
1191 TypeResult Parser::ParseBaseTypeSpecifier(SourceLocation &BaseLoc,
1192  SourceLocation &EndLocation) {
1193  // Ignore attempts to use typename
1194  if (Tok.is(tok::kw_typename)) {
1195  Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected_class_name_not_template)
1196  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(Tok.getLocation());
1197  ConsumeToken();
1198  }
1199 
1200  // Parse optional nested-name-specifier
1201  CXXScopeSpec SS;
1202  if (ParseOptionalCXXScopeSpecifier(SS, /*ObjectType=*/nullptr,
1203  /*ObjectHasErrors=*/false,
1204  /*EnteringContext=*/false))
1205  return true;
1206 
1207  BaseLoc = Tok.getLocation();
1208 
1209  // Parse decltype-specifier
1210  // tok == kw_decltype is just error recovery, it can only happen when SS
1211  // isn't empty
1212  if (Tok.isOneOf(tok::kw_decltype, tok::annot_decltype)) {
1213  if (SS.isNotEmpty())
1214  Diag(SS.getBeginLoc(), diag::err_unexpected_scope_on_base_decltype)
1215  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(SS.getRange());
1216  // Fake up a Declarator to use with ActOnTypeName.
1217  DeclSpec DS(AttrFactory);
1218 
1219  EndLocation = ParseDecltypeSpecifier(DS);
1220 
1221  Declarator DeclaratorInfo(DS, DeclaratorContext::TypeName);
1222  return Actions.ActOnTypeName(getCurScope(), DeclaratorInfo);
1223  }
1224 
1225  // Check whether we have a template-id that names a type.
1226  if (Tok.is(tok::annot_template_id)) {
1227  TemplateIdAnnotation *TemplateId = takeTemplateIdAnnotation(Tok);
1228  if (TemplateId->mightBeType()) {
1229  AnnotateTemplateIdTokenAsType(SS, /*IsClassName*/true);
1230 
1231  assert(Tok.is(tok::annot_typename) && "template-id -> type failed");
1232  TypeResult Type = getTypeAnnotation(Tok);
1233  EndLocation = Tok.getAnnotationEndLoc();
1234  ConsumeAnnotationToken();
1235  return Type;
1236  }
1237 
1238  // Fall through to produce an error below.
1239  }
1240 
1241  if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) {
1242  Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected_class_name);
1243  return true;
1244  }
1245 
1246  IdentifierInfo *Id = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
1247  SourceLocation IdLoc = ConsumeToken();
1248 
1249  if (Tok.is(tok::less)) {
1250  // It looks the user intended to write a template-id here, but the
1251  // template-name was wrong. Try to fix that.
1252  // FIXME: Invoke ParseOptionalCXXScopeSpecifier in a "'template' is neither
1253  // required nor permitted" mode, and do this there.
1254  TemplateNameKind TNK = TNK_Non_template;
1255  TemplateTy Template;
1256  if (!Actions.DiagnoseUnknownTemplateName(*Id, IdLoc, getCurScope(),
1257  &SS, Template, TNK)) {
1258  Diag(IdLoc, diag::err_unknown_template_name)
1259  << Id;
1260  }
1261 
1262  // Form the template name
1263  UnqualifiedId TemplateName;
1264  TemplateName.setIdentifier(Id, IdLoc);
1265 
1266  // Parse the full template-id, then turn it into a type.
1267  if (AnnotateTemplateIdToken(Template, TNK, SS, SourceLocation(),
1268  TemplateName))
1269  return true;
1270  if (Tok.is(tok::annot_template_id) &&
1271  takeTemplateIdAnnotation(Tok)->mightBeType())
1272  AnnotateTemplateIdTokenAsType(SS, /*IsClassName*/true);
1273 
1274  // If we didn't end up with a typename token, there's nothing more we
1275  // can do.
1276  if (Tok.isNot(tok::annot_typename))
1277  return true;
1278 
1279  // Retrieve the type from the annotation token, consume that token, and
1280  // return.
1281  EndLocation = Tok.getAnnotationEndLoc();
1282  TypeResult Type = getTypeAnnotation(Tok);
1283  ConsumeAnnotationToken();
1284  return Type;
1285  }
1286 
1287  // We have an identifier; check whether it is actually a type.
1288  IdentifierInfo *CorrectedII = nullptr;
1289  ParsedType Type = Actions.getTypeName(
1290  *Id, IdLoc, getCurScope(), &SS, /*isClassName=*/true, false, nullptr,
1291  /*IsCtorOrDtorName=*/false,
1292  /*WantNontrivialTypeSourceInfo=*/true,
1293  /*IsClassTemplateDeductionContext*/ false, &CorrectedII);
1294  if (!Type) {
1295  Diag(IdLoc, diag::err_expected_class_name);
1296  return true;
1297  }
1298 
1299  // Consume the identifier.
1300  EndLocation = IdLoc;
1301 
1302  // Fake up a Declarator to use with ActOnTypeName.
1303  DeclSpec DS(AttrFactory);
1304  DS.SetRangeStart(IdLoc);
1305  DS.SetRangeEnd(EndLocation);
1306  DS.getTypeSpecScope() = SS;
1307 
1308  const char *PrevSpec = nullptr;
1309  unsigned DiagID;
1310  DS.SetTypeSpecType(TST_typename, IdLoc, PrevSpec, DiagID, Type,
1311  Actions.getASTContext().getPrintingPolicy());
1312 
1313  Declarator DeclaratorInfo(DS, DeclaratorContext::TypeName);
1314  return Actions.ActOnTypeName(getCurScope(), DeclaratorInfo);
1315 }

1328 /// Determine whether the following tokens are valid after a type-specifier
1329 /// which could be a standalone declaration. This will conservatively return
1330 /// true if there's any doubt, and is appropriate for insert-';' fixits.
1331 bool Parser::isValidAfterTypeSpecifier(bool CouldBeBitfield) {
1332  // This switch enumerates the valid "follow" set for type-specifiers.
1333  switch (Tok.getKind()) {
1334  default: break;
1335  case tok::semi: // struct foo {...} ;
1336  case tok::star: // struct foo {...} * P;
1337  case tok::amp: // struct foo {...} & R = ...
1338  case tok::ampamp: // struct foo {...} && R = ...
1339  case tok::identifier: // struct foo {...} V ;
1340  case tok::r_paren: //(struct foo {...} ) {4}
1341  case tok::coloncolon: // struct foo {...} :: a::b;
1342  case tok::annot_cxxscope: // struct foo {...} a:: b;
1343  case tok::annot_typename: // struct foo {...} a ::b;
1344  case tok::annot_template_id: // struct foo {...} a<int> ::b;
1345  case tok::kw_decltype: // struct foo {...} decltype (a)::b;
1346  case tok::l_paren: // struct foo {...} ( x);
1347  case tok::comma: // __builtin_offsetof(struct foo{...} ,
1348  case tok::kw_operator: // struct foo operator ++() {...}
1349  case tok::kw___declspec: // struct foo {...} __declspec(...)
1350  case tok::l_square: // void f(struct f [ 3])
1351  case tok::ellipsis: // void f(struct f ... [Ns])
1352  // FIXME: we should emit semantic diagnostic when declaration
1353  // attribute is in type attribute position.
1354  case tok::kw___attribute: // struct foo __attribute__((used)) x;
1355  case tok::annot_pragma_pack: // struct foo {...} _Pragma(pack(pop));
1356  // struct foo {...} _Pragma(section(...));
1357  case tok::annot_pragma_ms_pragma:
1358  // struct foo {...} _Pragma(vtordisp(pop));
1359  case tok::annot_pragma_ms_vtordisp:
1360  // struct foo {...} _Pragma(pointers_to_members(...));
1361  case tok::annot_pragma_ms_pointers_to_members:
1362  return true;
1363  case tok::colon:
1364  return CouldBeBitfield || // enum E { ... } : 2;
1365  ColonIsSacred; // _Generic(..., enum E : 2);
1366  // Microsoft compatibility
1367  case tok::kw___cdecl: // struct foo {...} __cdecl x;
1368  case tok::kw___fastcall: // struct foo {...} __fastcall x;
1369  case tok::kw___stdcall: // struct foo {...} __stdcall x;
1370  case tok::kw___thiscall: // struct foo {...} __thiscall x;
1371  case tok::kw___vectorcall: // struct foo {...} __vectorcall x;
1372  // We will diagnose these calling-convention specifiers on non-function
1373  // declarations later, so claim they are valid after a type specifier.
1374  return getLangOpts().MicrosoftExt;
1375  // Type qualifiers
1376  case tok::kw_const: // struct foo {...} const x;
1377  case tok::kw_volatile: // struct foo {...} volatile x;
1378  case tok::kw_restrict: // struct foo {...} restrict x;
1379  case tok::kw__Atomic: // struct foo {...} _Atomic x;
1380  case tok::kw___unaligned: // struct foo {...} __unaligned *x;
1381  // Function specifiers
1382  // Note, no 'explicit'. An explicit function must be either a conversion
1383  // operator or a constructor. Either way, it can't have a return type.
1384  case tok::kw_inline: // struct foo inline f();
1385  case tok::kw_virtual: // struct foo virtual f();
1386  case tok::kw_friend: // struct foo friend f();
1387  // Storage-class specifiers
1388  case tok::kw_static: // struct foo {...} static x;
1389  case tok::kw_extern: // struct foo {...} extern x;
1390  case tok::kw_typedef: // struct foo {...} typedef x;
1391  case tok::kw_register: // struct foo {...} register x;
1392  case tok::kw_auto: // struct foo {...} auto x;
1393  case tok::kw_mutable: // struct foo {...} mutable x;
1394  case tok::kw_thread_local: // struct foo {...} thread_local x;
1395  case tok::kw_constexpr: // struct foo {...} constexpr x;
1396  case tok::kw_consteval: // struct foo {...} consteval x;
1397  case tok::kw_constinit: // struct foo {...} constinit x;
1398  // As shown above, type qualifiers and storage class specifiers absolutely
1399  // can occur after class specifiers according to the grammar. However,
1400  // almost no one actually writes code like this. If we see one of these,
1401  // it is much more likely that someone missed a semi colon and the
1402  // type/storage class specifier we're seeing is part of the *next*
1403  // intended declaration, as in:
1404  //
1405  // struct foo { ... }
1406  // typedef int X;
1407  //
1408  // We'd really like to emit a missing semicolon error instead of emitting
1409  // an error on the 'int' saying that you can't have two type specifiers in
1410  // the same declaration of X. Because of this, we look ahead past this
1411  // token to see if it's a type specifier. If so, we know the code is
1412  // otherwise invalid, so we can produce the expected semi error.
1413  if (!isKnownToBeTypeSpecifier(NextToken()))
1414  return true;
1415  break;
1416  case tok::r_brace: // struct bar { struct foo {...} }
1417  // Missing ';' at end of struct is accepted as an extension in C mode.
1418  if (!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
1419  return true;
1420  break;
1421  case tok::greater:
1422  // template<class T = class X>
1423  return getLangOpts().CPlusPlus;
1424  }
1425  return false;
1426 }

1428 /// ParseClassSpecifier - Parse a C++ class-specifier [C++ class] or
1429 /// elaborated-type-specifier [C++ dcl.type.elab]; we can't tell which
1430 /// until we reach the start of a definition or see a token that
1431 /// cannot start a definition.
1432 ///
1433 /// class-specifier: [C++ class]
1434 /// class-head '{' member-specification[opt] '}'
1435 /// class-head '{' member-specification[opt] '}' attributes[opt]

1437 /// class-key identifier[opt] base-clause[opt]
1438 /// class-key nested-name-specifier identifier base-clause[opt]

1440 /// base-clause[opt]

1725  // There are four options here.
1726  // - If we are in a trailing return type, this is always just a reference,
1727  // and we must not try to parse a definition. For instance,
1728  // [] () -> struct S { };
1729  // does not define a type.
1730  // - If we have 'struct foo {...', 'struct foo :...',
1731  // 'struct foo final :' or 'struct foo final {', then this is a definition.
1732  // - If we have 'struct foo;', then this is either a forward declaration
1733  // or a friend declaration, which have to be treated differently.
1734  // - Otherwise we have something like 'struct foo xyz', a reference.
1735  //
1736  // We also detect these erroneous cases to provide better diagnostic for
1737  // C++11 attributes parsing.
1738  // - attributes follow class name:
1739  // struct foo [[]] {};
1740  // - attributes appear before or after 'final':
1741  // struct foo [[]] final [[]] {};
1742  //
1743  // However, in type-specifier-seq's, things look like declarations but are
1744  // just references, e.g.
1745  // new struct s;
1746  // or
1747  // &T::operator struct s;
1748  // For these, DSC is DeclSpecContext::DSC_type_specifier or
1749  // DeclSpecContext::DSC_alias_declaration.
1750 
1751  // If there are attributes after class name, parse them.
1752  MaybeParseCXX11Attributes(Attributes);
1753 
1754  const PrintingPolicy &Policy = Actions.getASTContext().getPrintingPolicy();
1755  Sema::TagUseKind TUK;
1756  if (isDefiningTypeSpecifierContext(DSC) == AllowDefiningTypeSpec::No ||
1757  (getLangOpts().OpenMP && OpenMPDirectiveParsing))
1758  TUK = Sema::TUK_Reference;
1759  else if (Tok.is(tok::l_brace) ||
1760  (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && Tok.is(tok::colon)) ||
1761  (isClassCompatibleKeyword() &&
1762  (NextToken().is(tok::l_brace) || NextToken().is(tok::colon)))) {
1763  if (DS.isFriendSpecified()) {
1764  // C++ [class.friend]p2:
1765  // A class shall not be defined in a friend declaration.
1766  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_friend_decl_defines_type)
1767  << SourceRange(DS.getFriendSpecLoc());
1768 
1769  // Skip everything up to the semicolon, so that this looks like a proper
1770  // friend class (or template thereof) declaration.
1771  SkipUntil(tok::semi, StopBeforeMatch);
1772  TUK = Sema::TUK_Friend;
1773  } else {
1774  // Okay, this is a class definition.
1775  TUK = Sema::TUK_Definition;
1776  }
1777  } else if (isClassCompatibleKeyword() &&
1778  (NextToken().is(tok::l_square) ||
1779  NextToken().is(tok::kw_alignas) ||
1780  isCXX11VirtSpecifier(NextToken()) != VirtSpecifiers::VS_None)) {
1781  // We can't tell if this is a definition or reference
1782  // until we skipped the 'final' and C++11 attribute specifiers.
1783  TentativeParsingAction PA(*this);
1784 
1785  // Skip the 'final', abstract'... keywords.
1786  while (isClassCompatibleKeyword()) {
1787  ConsumeToken();
1788  }
1789 
1790  // Skip C++11 attribute specifiers.
1791  while (true) {
1792  if (Tok.is(tok::l_square) && NextToken().is(tok::l_square)) {
1793  ConsumeBracket();
1794  if (!SkipUntil(tok::r_square, StopAtSemi))
1795  break;
1796  } else if (Tok.is(tok::kw_alignas) && NextToken().is(tok::l_paren)) {
1797  ConsumeToken();
1798  ConsumeParen();
1799  if (!SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi))
1800  break;
1801  } else {
1802  break;
1803  }
1804  }
1805 
1806  if (Tok.isOneOf(tok::l_brace, tok::colon))
1807  TUK = Sema::TUK_Definition;
1808  else
1809  TUK = Sema::TUK_Reference;
1810 
1811  PA.Revert();
1812  } else if (!isTypeSpecifier(DSC) &&
1813  (Tok.is(tok::semi) ||
1814  (Tok.isAtStartOfLine() && !isValidAfterTypeSpecifier(false)))) {
1815  TUK = DS.isFriendSpecified() ? Sema::TUK_Friend : Sema::TUK_Declaration;
1816  if (Tok.isNot(tok::semi)) {
1817  const PrintingPolicy &PPol = Actions.getASTContext().getPrintingPolicy();
1818  // A semicolon was missing after this declaration. Diagnose and recover.
1819  ExpectAndConsume(tok::semi, diag::err_expected_after,
1820  DeclSpec::getSpecifierName(TagType, PPol));
1821  PP.EnterToken(Tok, /*IsReinject*/true);
1822  Tok.setKind(tok::semi);
1823  }
1824  } else
1825  TUK = Sema::TUK_Reference;
1826 
1827  // Forbid misplaced attributes. In cases of a reference, we pass attributes
1828  // to caller to handle.
1829  if (TUK != Sema::TUK_Reference) {
1830  // If this is not a reference, then the only possible
1831  // valid place for C++11 attributes to appear here
1832  // is between class-key and class-name. If there are
1833  // any attributes after class-name, we try a fixit to move
1834  // them to the right place.
1835  SourceRange AttrRange = Attributes.Range;
1836  if (AttrRange.isValid()) {
1837  Diag(AttrRange.getBegin(), diag::err_attributes_not_allowed)
1838  << AttrRange
1839  << FixItHint::CreateInsertionFromRange(AttrFixitLoc,
1840  CharSourceRange(AttrRange, true))
1841  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(AttrRange);
1842 
1843  // Recover by adding misplaced attributes to the attribute list
1844  // of the class so they can be applied on the class later.
1845  attrs.takeAllFrom(Attributes);
1846  }
1847  }
1848 
1849  if (!Name && !TemplateId && (DS.getTypeSpecType() == DeclSpec::TST_error ||
1850  TUK != Sema::TUK_Definition)) {
1851  if (DS.getTypeSpecType() != DeclSpec::TST_error) {
1852  // We have a declaration or reference to an anonymous class.
1853  Diag(StartLoc, diag::err_anon_type_definition)
1854  << DeclSpec::getSpecifierName(TagType, Policy);
1855  }
1856 
1857  // If we are parsing a definition and stop at a base-clause, continue on
1858  // until the semicolon. Continuing from the comma will just trick us into
1859  // thinking we are seeing a variable declaration.
1860  if (TUK == Sema::TUK_Definition && Tok.is(tok::colon))
1861  SkipUntil(tok::semi, StopBeforeMatch);
1862  else
1863  SkipUntil(tok::comma, StopAtSemi);
1864  return;
1865  }
1866 
1867  // Create the tag portion of the class or class template.
1868  DeclResult TagOrTempResult = true; // invalid
1869  TypeResult TypeResult = true; // invalid
1870 
1871  bool Owned = false;
1872  Sema::SkipBodyInfo SkipBody;
1873  if (TemplateId) {
1874  // Explicit specialization, class template partial specialization,
1875  // or explicit instantiation.
1876  ASTTemplateArgsPtr TemplateArgsPtr(TemplateId->getTemplateArgs(),
1877  TemplateId->NumArgs);
1878  if (TemplateId->isInvalid()) {
1879  // Can't build the declaration.
1880  } else if (TemplateInfo.Kind == ParsedTemplateInfo::ExplicitInstantiation &&
1881  TUK == Sema::TUK_Declaration) {
1882  // This is an explicit instantiation of a class template.
1883  ProhibitCXX11Attributes(attrs, diag::err_attributes_not_allowed,
1884  /*DiagnoseEmptyAttrs=*/true);
1885 
1886  TagOrTempResult = Actions.ActOnExplicitInstantiation(
1887  getCurScope(), TemplateInfo.ExternLoc, TemplateInfo.TemplateLoc,
1888  TagType, StartLoc, SS, TemplateId->Template,
1889  TemplateId->TemplateNameLoc, TemplateId->LAngleLoc, TemplateArgsPtr,
1890  TemplateId->RAngleLoc, attrs);
1891 
1892  // Friend template-ids are treated as references unless
1893  // they have template headers, in which case they're ill-formed
1894  // (FIXME: "template <class T> friend class A<T>::B<int>;").
1895  // We diagnose this error in ActOnClassTemplateSpecialization.
1896  } else if (TUK == Sema::TUK_Reference ||
1897  (TUK == Sema::TUK_Friend &&
1898  TemplateInfo.Kind == ParsedTemplateInfo::NonTemplate)) {
1899  ProhibitCXX11Attributes(attrs, diag::err_attributes_not_allowed,
1900  /*DiagnoseEmptyAttrs=*/true);
1901  TypeResult = Actions.ActOnTagTemplateIdType(TUK, TagType, StartLoc,
1902  SS,
1903  TemplateId->TemplateKWLoc,
1904  TemplateId->Template,
1905  TemplateId->TemplateNameLoc,
1906  TemplateId->LAngleLoc,
1907  TemplateArgsPtr,
1908  TemplateId->RAngleLoc);
1909  } else {
1910  // This is an explicit specialization or a class template
1911  // partial specialization.
1912  TemplateParameterLists FakedParamLists;
1913  if (TemplateInfo.Kind == ParsedTemplateInfo::ExplicitInstantiation) {
1914  // This looks like an explicit instantiation, because we have
1915  // something like
1916  //
1917  // template class Foo<X>
1918  //
1919  // but it actually has a definition. Most likely, this was
1920  // meant to be an explicit specialization, but the user forgot
1921  // the '<>' after 'template'.
1922  // It this is friend declaration however, since it cannot have a
1923  // template header, it is most likely that the user meant to
1924  // remove the 'template' keyword.
1925  assert((TUK == Sema::TUK_Definition || TUK == Sema::TUK_Friend) &&
1926  "Expected a definition here");
1927 
1928  if (TUK == Sema::TUK_Friend) {
1929  Diag(DS.getFriendSpecLoc(), diag::err_friend_explicit_instantiation);
1930  TemplateParams = nullptr;
1931  } else {
1932  SourceLocation LAngleLoc =
1933  PP.getLocForEndOfToken(TemplateInfo.TemplateLoc);
1934  Diag(TemplateId->TemplateNameLoc,
1935  diag::err_explicit_instantiation_with_definition)
1936  << SourceRange(TemplateInfo.TemplateLoc)
1937  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(LAngleLoc, "<>");
1938 
1939  // Create a fake template parameter list that contains only
1940  // "template<>", so that we treat this construct as a class
1941  // template specialization.
1942  FakedParamLists.push_back(Actions.ActOnTemplateParameterList(
1943  0, SourceLocation(), TemplateInfo.TemplateLoc, LAngleLoc, None,
1944  LAngleLoc, nullptr));
1945  TemplateParams = &FakedParamLists;
1946  }
1947  }
1948 
1949  // Build the class template specialization.
1950  TagOrTempResult = Actions.ActOnClassTemplateSpecialization(
1951  getCurScope(), TagType, TUK, StartLoc, DS.getModulePrivateSpecLoc(),
1952  SS, *TemplateId, attrs,
1953  MultiTemplateParamsArg(TemplateParams ? &(*TemplateParams)[0]
1954  : nullptr,
1955  TemplateParams ? TemplateParams->size() : 0),
1956  &SkipBody);
1957  }
1958  } else if (TemplateInfo.Kind == ParsedTemplateInfo::ExplicitInstantiation &&
1959  TUK == Sema::TUK_Declaration) {
1960  // Explicit instantiation of a member of a class template
1961  // specialization, e.g.,
1962  //
1963  // template struct Outer<int>::Inner;
1964  //
1965  ProhibitAttributes(attrs);
1966 
1967  TagOrTempResult = Actions.ActOnExplicitInstantiation(
1968  getCurScope(), TemplateInfo.ExternLoc, TemplateInfo.TemplateLoc,
1969  TagType, StartLoc, SS, Name, NameLoc, attrs);
1970  } else if (TUK == Sema::TUK_Friend &&
1971  TemplateInfo.Kind != ParsedTemplateInfo::NonTemplate) {
1972  ProhibitCXX11Attributes(attrs, diag::err_attributes_not_allowed,
1973  /*DiagnoseEmptyAttrs=*/true);
1974 
1975  TagOrTempResult = Actions.ActOnTemplatedFriendTag(
1976  getCurScope(), DS.getFriendSpecLoc(), TagType, StartLoc, SS, Name,
1977  NameLoc, attrs,
1978  MultiTemplateParamsArg(TemplateParams ? &(*TemplateParams)[0] : nullptr,
1979  TemplateParams ? TemplateParams->size() : 0));
1980  } else {
1981  if (TUK != Sema::TUK_Declaration && TUK != Sema::TUK_Definition)
1982  ProhibitCXX11Attributes(attrs, diag::err_attributes_not_allowed,
1983  /* DiagnoseEmptyAttrs=*/true);
1984 
1985  if (TUK == Sema::TUK_Definition &&
1986  TemplateInfo.Kind == ParsedTemplateInfo::ExplicitInstantiation) {
1987  // If the declarator-id is not a template-id, issue a diagnostic and
1988  // recover by ignoring the 'template' keyword.
1989  Diag(Tok, diag::err_template_defn_explicit_instantiation)
1990  << 1 << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(TemplateInfo.TemplateLoc);
1991  TemplateParams = nullptr;
1992  }
1993 
1994  bool IsDependent = false;
1995 
1996  // Don't pass down template parameter lists if this is just a tag
1997  // reference. For example, we don't need the template parameters here:
1998  // template <class T> class A *makeA(T t);
1999  MultiTemplateParamsArg TParams;
2000  if (TUK != Sema::TUK_Reference && TemplateParams)
2001  TParams =
2002  MultiTemplateParamsArg(&(*TemplateParams)[0], TemplateParams->size());
2003 
2004  stripTypeAttributesOffDeclSpec(attrs, DS, TUK);
2005 
2006  // Declaration or definition of a class type
2007  TagOrTempResult = Actions.ActOnTag(
2008  getCurScope(), TagType, TUK, StartLoc, SS, Name, NameLoc, attrs, AS,
2009  DS.getModulePrivateSpecLoc(), TParams, Owned, IsDependent,
2010  SourceLocation(), false, clang::TypeResult(),
2011  DSC == DeclSpecContext::DSC_type_specifier,
2012  DSC == DeclSpecContext::DSC_template_param ||
2013  DSC == DeclSpecContext::DSC_template_type_arg,
2014  &SkipBody);
2015 
2016  // If ActOnTag said the type was dependent, try again with the
2017  // less common call.
2018  if (IsDependent) {
2019  assert(TUK == Sema::TUK_Reference || TUK == Sema::TUK_Friend);
2020  TypeResult = Actions.ActOnDependentTag(getCurScope(), TagType, TUK,
2021  SS, Name, StartLoc, NameLoc);
2022  }
2023  }
2024 
2025  // If this is an elaborated type specifier in function template,
2026  // and we delayed diagnostics before,
2027  // just merge them into the current pool.
2028  if (shouldDelayDiagsInTag) {
2029  diagsFromTag.done();
2030  if (TUK == Sema::TUK_Reference &&
2031  TemplateInfo.Kind == ParsedTemplateInfo::Template)
2032  diagsFromTag.redelay();
2033  }
2034 
2035  // If there is a body, parse it and inform the actions module.
2036  if (TUK == Sema::TUK_Definition) {
2037  assert(Tok.is(tok::l_brace) ||
2038  (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && Tok.is(tok::colon)) ||
2039  isClassCompatibleKeyword());
2040  if (SkipBody.ShouldSkip)
2041  SkipCXXMemberSpecification(StartLoc, AttrFixitLoc, TagType,
2042  TagOrTempResult.get());
2043  else if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
2044  ParseCXXMemberSpecification(StartLoc, AttrFixitLoc, attrs, TagType,
2045  TagOrTempResult.get());
2046  else {
2047  Decl *D =
2048  SkipBody.CheckSameAsPrevious ? SkipBody.New : TagOrTempResult.get();
2049  // Parse the definition body.
2050  ParseStructUnionBody(StartLoc, TagType, cast<RecordDecl>(D));
2051  if (SkipBody.CheckSameAsPrevious &&
2052  !Actions.ActOnDuplicateDefinition(DS, TagOrTempResult.get(),
2053  SkipBody)) {
2054  DS.SetTypeSpecError();
2055  return;
2056  }
2057  }
2058  }
2059 
2060  if (!TagOrTempResult.isInvalid())
2061  // Delayed processing of attributes.
2062  Actions.ProcessDeclAttributeDelayed(TagOrTempResult.get(), attrs);
2063 
2064  const char *PrevSpec = nullptr;
2065  unsigned DiagID;
2066  bool Result;
2067  if (!TypeResult.isInvalid()) {
2068  Result = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_typename, StartLoc,
2069  NameLoc.isValid() ? NameLoc : StartLoc,
2070  PrevSpec, DiagID, TypeResult.get(), Policy);
2071  } else if (!TagOrTempResult.isInvalid()) {
2072  Result = DS.SetTypeSpecType(TagType, StartLoc,
2073  NameLoc.isValid() ? NameLoc : StartLoc,
2074  PrevSpec, DiagID, TagOrTempResult.get(), Owned,
2075  Policy);
2076  } else {
2077  DS.SetTypeSpecError();
2078  return;
2079  }
2080 
2081  if (Result)
2082  Diag(StartLoc, DiagID) << PrevSpec;
2083 
2084  // At this point, we've successfully parsed a class-specifier in 'definition'
2085  // form (e.g. "struct foo { int x; }". While we could just return here, we're
2086  // going to look at what comes after it to improve error recovery. If an
2087  // impossible token occurs next, we assume that the programmer forgot a ; at
2088  // the end of the declaration and recover that way.
2089  //
2090  // Also enforce C++ [temp]p3:
2091  // In a template-declaration which defines a class, no declarator
2092  // is permitted.
2093  //
2094  // After a type-specifier, we don't expect a semicolon. This only happens in
2095  // C, since definitions are not permitted in this context in C++.
2096  if (TUK == Sema::TUK_Definition &&
2097  (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus || !isTypeSpecifier(DSC)) &&
2098  (TemplateInfo.Kind || !isValidAfterTypeSpecifier(false))) {
2099  if (Tok.isNot(tok::semi)) {
2100  const PrintingPolicy &PPol = Actions.getASTContext().getPrintingPolicy();
2101  ExpectAndConsume(tok::semi, diag::err_expected_after,
2102  DeclSpec::getSpecifierName(TagType, PPol));
2103  // Push this token back into the preprocessor and change our current token
2104  // to ';' so that the rest of the code recovers as though there were an
2105  // ';' after the definition.
2106  PP.EnterToken(Tok, /*IsReinject=*/true);
2107  Tok.setKind(tok::semi);
2108  }
2109  }
2110 }

2112 /// ParseBaseClause - Parse the base-clause of a C++ class [C++ class.derived].
2113 ///
2114 /// base-clause : [C++ class.derived]
2115 /// ':' base-specifier-list
2116 /// base-specifier-list:
2117 /// base-specifier '...'[opt]
2118 /// base-specifier-list ',' base-specifier '...'[opt]
2119 void Parser::ParseBaseClause(Decl *ClassDecl) {
2120  assert(Tok.is(tok::colon) && "Not a base clause");
2121  ConsumeToken();
2122 
2123  // Build up an array of parsed base specifiers.
2124  SmallVector<CXXBaseSpecifier *, 8> BaseInfo;
2125 
2126  while (true) {
2127  // Parse a base-specifier.
2128  BaseResult Result = ParseBaseSpecifier(ClassDecl);
2129  if (Result.isInvalid()) {
2130  // Skip the rest of this base specifier, up until the comma or
2131  // opening brace.
2132  SkipUntil(tok::comma, tok::l_brace, StopAtSemi | StopBeforeMatch);
2133  } else {
2134  // Add this to our array of base specifiers.
2135  BaseInfo.push_back(Result.get());
2136  }
2137 
2138  // If the next token is a comma, consume it and keep reading
2139  // base-specifiers.
2140  if (!TryConsumeToken(tok::comma))
2141  break;
2142  }
2143 
2144  // Attach the base specifiers
2145  Actions.ActOnBaseSpecifiers(ClassDecl, BaseInfo);
2146 }

2148 /// ParseBaseSpecifier - Parse a C++ base-specifier. A base-specifier is
2149 /// one entry in the base class list of a class specifier, for example:
2150 /// class foo : public bar, virtual private baz {
2151 /// 'public bar' and 'virtual private baz' are each base-specifiers.
2152 ///
2153 /// base-specifier: [C++ class.derived]
2154 /// attribute-specifier-seq[opt] base-type-specifier
2155 /// attribute-specifier-seq[opt] 'virtual' access-specifier[opt]
2156 /// base-type-specifier
2157 /// attribute-specifier-seq[opt] access-specifier 'virtual'[opt]
2158 /// base-type-specifier
2159 BaseResult Parser::ParseBaseSpecifier(Decl *ClassDecl) {
2160  bool IsVirtual = false;
2161  SourceLocation StartLoc = Tok.getLocation();
2162 
2163  ParsedAttributes Attributes(AttrFactory);
2164  MaybeParseCXX11Attributes(Attributes);
2165 
2166  // Parse the 'virtual' keyword.
2167  if (TryConsumeToken(tok::kw_virtual))
2168  IsVirtual = true;
2169 
2170  CheckMisplacedCXX11Attribute(Attributes, StartLoc);
2171 
2172  // Parse an (optional) access specifier.
2173  AccessSpecifier Access = getAccessSpecifierIfPresent();
2174  if (Access != AS_none)
2175  ConsumeToken();
2176 
2177  CheckMisplacedCXX11Attribute(Attributes, StartLoc);
2178 
2179  // Parse the 'virtual' keyword (again!), in case it came after the
2180  // access specifier.
2181  if (Tok.is(tok::kw_virtual)) {
2182  SourceLocation VirtualLoc = ConsumeToken();
2183  if (IsVirtual) {
2184  // Complain about duplicate 'virtual'
2185  Diag(VirtualLoc, diag::err_dup_virtual)
2186  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(VirtualLoc);
2187  }
2188 
2189  IsVirtual = true;
2190  }
2191 
2192  CheckMisplacedCXX11Attribute(Attributes, StartLoc);
2193 
2194  // Parse the class-name.
2195 
2196  // HACK: MSVC doesn't consider _Atomic to be a keyword and its STL
2197  // implementation for VS2013 uses _Atomic as an identifier for one of the
2198  // classes in <atomic>. Treat '_Atomic' to be an identifier when we are
2199  // parsing the class-name for a base specifier.
2200  if (getLangOpts().MSVCCompat && Tok.is(tok::kw__Atomic) &&
2201  NextToken().is(tok::less))
2202  Tok.setKind(tok::identifier);
2203 
2204  SourceLocation EndLocation;
2205  SourceLocation BaseLoc;
2206  TypeResult BaseType = ParseBaseTypeSpecifier(BaseLoc, EndLocation);
2207  if (BaseType.isInvalid())
2208  return true;
2209 
2210  // Parse the optional ellipsis (for a pack expansion). The ellipsis is
2211  // actually part of the base-specifier-list grammar productions, but we
2212  // parse it here for convenience.
2213  SourceLocation EllipsisLoc;
2214  TryConsumeToken(tok::ellipsis, EllipsisLoc);
2215 
2216  // Find the complete source range for the base-specifier.
2217  SourceRange Range(StartLoc, EndLocation);
2218 
2219  // Notify semantic analysis that we have parsed a complete
2220  // base-specifier.
2221  return Actions.ActOnBaseSpecifier(ClassDecl, Range, Attributes, IsVirtual,
2222  Access, BaseType.get(), BaseLoc,
2223  EllipsisLoc);
2224 }

2226 /// getAccessSpecifierIfPresent - Determine whether the next token is
2227 /// a C++ access-specifier.
2228 ///
2229 /// access-specifier: [C++ class.derived]
2230 /// 'private'
2231 /// 'protected'
2232 /// 'public'
2233 AccessSpecifier Parser::getAccessSpecifierIfPresent() const {
2234  switch (Tok.getKind()) {
2235  default: return AS_none;
2236  case tok::kw_private: return AS_private;
2237  case tok::kw_protected: return AS_protected;
2238  case tok::kw_public: return AS_public;
2239  }
2240 }

2242 /// If the given declarator has any parts for which parsing has to be
2243 /// delayed, e.g., default arguments or an exception-specification, create a
2244 /// late-parsed method declaration record to handle the parsing at the end of
2245 /// the class definition.
2246 void Parser::HandleMemberFunctionDeclDelays(Declarator& DeclaratorInfo,
2247  Decl *ThisDecl) {
2248  DeclaratorChunk::FunctionTypeInfo &FTI
2249  = DeclaratorInfo.getFunctionTypeInfo();
2250  // If there was a late-parsed exception-specification, we'll need a
2251  // late parse
2252  bool NeedLateParse = FTI.getExceptionSpecType() == EST_Unparsed;
2253 
2254  if (!NeedLateParse) {
2255  // Look ahead to see if there are any default args
2256  for (unsigned ParamIdx = 0; ParamIdx < FTI.NumParams; ++ParamIdx) {
2257  auto Param = cast<ParmVarDecl>(FTI.Params[ParamIdx].Param);
2258  if (Param->hasUnparsedDefaultArg()) {
2259  NeedLateParse = true;
2260  break;
2261  }
2262  }
2263  }
2264 
2265  if (NeedLateParse) {
2266  // Push this method onto the stack of late-parsed method
2267  // declarations.
2268  auto LateMethod = new LateParsedMethodDeclaration(this, ThisDecl);
2269  getCurrentClass().LateParsedDeclarations.push_back(LateMethod);
2270 
2271  // Push tokens for each parameter. Those that do not have defaults will be
2272  // NULL. We need to track all the parameters so that we can push them into
2273  // scope for later parameters and perhaps for the exception specification.
2274  LateMethod->DefaultArgs.reserve(FTI.NumParams);
2275  for (unsigned ParamIdx = 0; ParamIdx < FTI.NumParams; ++ParamIdx)
2276  LateMethod->DefaultArgs.push_back(LateParsedDefaultArgument(
2277  FTI.Params[ParamIdx].Param,
2278  std::move(FTI.Params[ParamIdx].DefaultArgTokens)));
2279 
2280  // Stash the exception-specification tokens in the late-pased method.
2281  if (FTI.getExceptionSpecType() == EST_Unparsed) {
2282  LateMethod->ExceptionSpecTokens = FTI.ExceptionSpecTokens;
2283  FTI.ExceptionSpecTokens = nullptr;
2284  }
2285  }
2286 }

2288 /// isCXX11VirtSpecifier - Determine whether the given token is a C++11
2289 /// virt-specifier.
2290 ///
2291 /// virt-specifier:
2292 /// override
2293 /// final
2294 /// __final
2295 VirtSpecifiers::Specifier Parser::isCXX11VirtSpecifier(const Token &Tok) const {
2296  if (!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus || Tok.isNot(tok::identifier))
2297  return VirtSpecifiers::VS_None;
2298 
2299  IdentifierInfo *II = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
2300 
2301  // Initialize the contextual keywords.
2302  if (!Ident_final) {
2303  Ident_final = &PP.getIdentifierTable().get("final");
2304  if (getLangOpts().GNUKeywords)
2305  Ident_GNU_final = &PP.getIdentifierTable().get("__final");
2306  if (getLangOpts().MicrosoftExt) {
2307  Ident_sealed = &PP.getIdentifierTable().get("sealed");
2308  Ident_abstract = &PP.getIdentifierTable().get("abstract");
2309  }
2310  Ident_override = &PP.getIdentifierTable().get("override");
2311  }
2312 
2313  if (II == Ident_override)
2314  return VirtSpecifiers::VS_Override;
2315 
2316  if (II == Ident_sealed)
2317  return VirtSpecifiers::VS_Sealed;
2318 
2319  if (II == Ident_abstract)
2320  return VirtSpecifiers::VS_Abstract;
2321 
2322  if (II == Ident_final)
2323  return VirtSpecifiers::VS_Final;
2324 
2325  if (II == Ident_GNU_final)
2326  return VirtSpecifiers::VS_GNU_Final;
2327 
2328  return VirtSpecifiers::VS_None;
2329 }

2331 /// ParseOptionalCXX11VirtSpecifierSeq - Parse a virt-specifier-seq.
2332 ///
2333 /// virt-specifier-seq:
2334 /// virt-specifier
2335 /// virt-specifier-seq virt-specifier
2336 void Parser::ParseOptionalCXX11VirtSpecifierSeq(VirtSpecifiers &VS,
2337  bool IsInterface,
2338  SourceLocation FriendLoc) {
2339  while (true) {
2340  VirtSpecifiers::Specifier Specifier = isCXX11VirtSpecifier();
2341  if (Specifier == VirtSpecifiers::VS_None)
2342  return;
2343 
2344  if (FriendLoc.isValid()) {
2345  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_friend_decl_spec)
2346  << VirtSpecifiers::getSpecifierName(Specifier)
2347  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(Tok.getLocation())
2348  << SourceRange(FriendLoc, FriendLoc);
2349  ConsumeToken();
2350  continue;
2351  }
2352 
2353  // C++ [class.mem]p8:
2354  // A virt-specifier-seq shall contain at most one of each virt-specifier.
2355  const char *PrevSpec = nullptr;
2356  if (VS.SetSpecifier(Specifier, Tok.getLocation(), PrevSpec))
2357  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_duplicate_virt_specifier)
2358  << PrevSpec
2359  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(Tok.getLocation());
2360 
2361  if (IsInterface && (Specifier == VirtSpecifiers::VS_Final ||
2362  Specifier == VirtSpecifiers::VS_Sealed)) {
2363  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_override_control_interface)
2364  << VirtSpecifiers::getSpecifierName(Specifier);
2365  } else if (Specifier == VirtSpecifiers::VS_Sealed) {
2366  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::ext_ms_sealed_keyword);
2367  } else if (Specifier == VirtSpecifiers::VS_Abstract) {
2368  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::ext_ms_abstract_keyword);
2369  } else if (Specifier == VirtSpecifiers::VS_GNU_Final) {
2370  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::ext_warn_gnu_final);
2371  } else {
2372  Diag(Tok.getLocation(),
2373  getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11
2374  ? diag::warn_cxx98_compat_override_control_keyword
2375  : diag::ext_override_control_keyword)
2376  << VirtSpecifiers::getSpecifierName(Specifier);
2377  }
2378  ConsumeToken();
2379  }
2380 }

2383 /// 'final' or Microsoft 'sealed' contextual keyword.
2384 bool Parser::isCXX11FinalKeyword() const {
2385  VirtSpecifiers::Specifier Specifier = isCXX11VirtSpecifier();
2386  return Specifier == VirtSpecifiers::VS_Final ||
2387  Specifier == VirtSpecifiers::VS_GNU_Final ||
2388  Specifier == VirtSpecifiers::VS_Sealed;
2389 }

2391 /// isClassCompatibleKeyword - Determine whether the next token is a C++11
2392 /// 'final' or Microsoft 'sealed' or 'abstract' contextual keywords.
2393 bool Parser::isClassCompatibleKeyword() const {
2394  VirtSpecifiers::Specifier Specifier = isCXX11VirtSpecifier();
2395  return Specifier == VirtSpecifiers::VS_Final ||
