2401 /// Parse a C++ member-declarator up to, but not including, the optional
2402 /// brace-or-equal-initializer or pure-specifier.
2403 bool Parser::ParseCXXMemberDeclaratorBeforeInitializer(
2404  Declarator &DeclaratorInfo, VirtSpecifiers &VS, ExprResult &BitfieldSize,
2405  LateParsedAttrList &LateParsedAttrs) {
2406  // member-declarator:
2407  // declarator virt-specifier-seq[opt] pure-specifier[opt]
2408  // declarator requires-clause
2409  // declarator brace-or-equal-initializer[opt]
2410  // identifier attribute-specifier-seq[opt] ':' constant-expression
2411  // brace-or-equal-initializer[opt]
2412  // ':' constant-expression
2413  //
2414  // NOTE: the latter two productions are a proposed bugfix rather than the
2415  // current grammar rules as of C++20.
2416  if (Tok.isNot(tok::colon))
2417  ParseDeclarator(DeclaratorInfo);
2418  else
2419  DeclaratorInfo.SetIdentifier(nullptr, Tok.getLocation());
2420 
2421  if (!DeclaratorInfo.isFunctionDeclarator() && TryConsumeToken(tok::colon)) {
2422  assert(DeclaratorInfo.isPastIdentifier() &&
2423  "don't know where identifier would go yet?");
2424  BitfieldSize = ParseConstantExpression();
2425  if (BitfieldSize.isInvalid())
2426  SkipUntil(tok::comma, StopAtSemi | StopBeforeMatch);
2427  } else if (Tok.is(tok::kw_requires)) {
2428  ParseTrailingRequiresClause(DeclaratorInfo);
2429  } else {
2430  ParseOptionalCXX11VirtSpecifierSeq(
2431  VS, getCurrentClass().IsInterface,
2432  DeclaratorInfo.getDeclSpec().getFriendSpecLoc());
2433  if (!VS.isUnset())
2434  MaybeParseAndDiagnoseDeclSpecAfterCXX11VirtSpecifierSeq(DeclaratorInfo, VS);
2435  }
2436 
2437  // If a simple-asm-expr is present, parse it.
2438  if (Tok.is(tok::kw_asm)) {
2439  SourceLocation Loc;
2440  ExprResult AsmLabel(ParseSimpleAsm(/*ForAsmLabel*/ true, &Loc));
2441  if (AsmLabel.isInvalid())
2442  SkipUntil(tok::comma, StopAtSemi | StopBeforeMatch);
2443 
2444  DeclaratorInfo.setAsmLabel(AsmLabel.get());
2445  DeclaratorInfo.SetRangeEnd(Loc);
2446  }
2447 
2448  // If attributes exist after the declarator, but before an '{', parse them.
2449  // However, this does not apply for [[]] attributes (which could show up
2450  // before or after the __attribute__ attributes).
2451  DiagnoseAndSkipCXX11Attributes();
2452  MaybeParseGNUAttributes(DeclaratorInfo, &LateParsedAttrs);
2453  DiagnoseAndSkipCXX11Attributes();
2454 
2455  // For compatibility with code written to older Clang, also accept a
2456  // virt-specifier *after* the GNU attributes.
2457  if (BitfieldSize.isUnset() && VS.isUnset()) {
2458  ParseOptionalCXX11VirtSpecifierSeq(
2459  VS, getCurrentClass().IsInterface,
2460  DeclaratorInfo.getDeclSpec().getFriendSpecLoc());
2461  if (!VS.isUnset()) {
2462  // If we saw any GNU-style attributes that are known to GCC followed by a
2463  // virt-specifier, issue a GCC-compat warning.
2464  for (const ParsedAttr &AL : DeclaratorInfo.getAttributes())
2465  if (AL.isKnownToGCC() && !AL.isCXX11Attribute())
2466  Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_gcc_attribute_location);
2467 
2468  MaybeParseAndDiagnoseDeclSpecAfterCXX11VirtSpecifierSeq(DeclaratorInfo, VS);
2469  }
2470  }
2471 
2472  // If this has neither a name nor a bit width, something has gone seriously
2473  // wrong. Skip until the semi-colon or }.
2474  if (!DeclaratorInfo.hasName() && BitfieldSize.isUnset()) {
2475  // If so, skip until the semi-colon or a }.
2476  SkipUntil(tok::r_brace, StopAtSemi | StopBeforeMatch);
2477  return true;
2478  }
2479  return false;
2480 }
2481 
2482 /// Look for declaration specifiers possibly occurring after C++11
2483 /// virt-specifier-seq and diagnose them.
2484 void Parser::MaybeParseAndDiagnoseDeclSpecAfterCXX11VirtSpecifierSeq(
2485  Declarator &D,
2486  VirtSpecifiers &VS) {
2487  DeclSpec DS(AttrFactory);
2488 
2489  // GNU-style and C++11 attributes are not allowed here, but they will be
2490  // handled by the caller. Diagnose everything else.
2491  ParseTypeQualifierListOpt(
2492  DS, AR_NoAttributesParsed, false,
2493  /*IdentifierRequired=*/false, llvm::function_ref<void()>([&]() {
2494  Actions.CodeCompleteFunctionQualifiers(DS, D, &VS);
2495  }));
2496  D.ExtendWithDeclSpec(DS);
2497 
2498  if (D.isFunctionDeclarator()) {
2499  auto &Function = D.getFunctionTypeInfo();
2500  if (DS.getTypeQualifiers() != DeclSpec::TQ_unspecified) {
2501  auto DeclSpecCheck = [&](DeclSpec::TQ TypeQual, StringRef FixItName,
2502  SourceLocation SpecLoc) {
2503  FixItHint Insertion;
2504  auto &MQ = Function.getOrCreateMethodQualifiers();
2505  if (!(MQ.getTypeQualifiers() & TypeQual)) {
2506  std::string Name(FixItName.data());
2507  Name += " ";
2508  Insertion = FixItHint::CreateInsertion(VS.getFirstLocation(), Name);
2509  MQ.SetTypeQual(TypeQual, SpecLoc);
2510  }
2511  Diag(SpecLoc, diag::err_declspec_after_virtspec)
2512  << FixItName
2513  << VirtSpecifiers::getSpecifierName(VS.getLastSpecifier())
2514  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(SpecLoc) << Insertion;
2515  };
2516  DS.forEachQualifier(DeclSpecCheck);
2517  }
2518 
2519  // Parse ref-qualifiers.
2520  bool RefQualifierIsLValueRef = true;
2521  SourceLocation RefQualifierLoc;
2522  if (ParseRefQualifier(RefQualifierIsLValueRef, RefQualifierLoc)) {
2523  const char *Name = (RefQualifierIsLValueRef ? "& " : "&& ");
2524  FixItHint Insertion = FixItHint::CreateInsertion(VS.getFirstLocation(), Name);
2525  Function.RefQualifierIsLValueRef = RefQualifierIsLValueRef;
2526  Function.RefQualifierLoc = RefQualifierLoc;
2527 
2528  Diag(RefQualifierLoc, diag::err_declspec_after_virtspec)
2529  << (RefQualifierIsLValueRef ? "&" : "&&")
2530  << VirtSpecifiers::getSpecifierName(VS.getLastSpecifier())
2531  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(RefQualifierLoc)
2532  << Insertion;
2533  D.SetRangeEnd(RefQualifierLoc);
2534  }
2535  }
2536 }

2538 /// ParseCXXClassMemberDeclaration - Parse a C++ class member declaration.
2539 ///
2540 /// member-declaration:
2541 /// decl-specifier-seq[opt] member-declarator-list[opt] ';'
2542 /// function-definition ';'[opt]
2543 /// ::[opt] nested-name-specifier template[opt] unqualified-id ';'[TODO]
2544 /// using-declaration [TODO]
2545 /// [C++0x] static_assert-declaration
2546 /// template-declaration
2547 /// [GNU] '__extension__' member-declaration
2548 ///
2549 /// member-declarator-list:
2550 /// member-declarator
2551 /// member-declarator-list ',' member-declarator
2552 ///
2553 /// member-declarator:
2554 /// declarator virt-specifier-seq[opt] pure-specifier[opt]
2555 /// [C++2a] declarator requires-clause
2556 /// declarator constant-initializer[opt]
2557 /// [C++11] declarator brace-or-equal-initializer[opt]
2558 /// identifier[opt] ':' constant-expression
2559 ///
2560 /// virt-specifier-seq:
2561 /// virt-specifier
2562 /// virt-specifier-seq virt-specifier
2563 ///
2564 /// virt-specifier:
2565 /// override
2566 /// final
2567 /// [MS] sealed
2568 ///
2569 /// pure-specifier:
2570 /// '= 0'
2571 ///
2572 /// constant-initializer:
2573 /// '=' constant-expression
2574 ///
2575 Parser::DeclGroupPtrTy
2576 Parser::ParseCXXClassMemberDeclaration(AccessSpecifier AS,
2577  ParsedAttributes &AccessAttrs,
2578  const ParsedTemplateInfo &TemplateInfo,
2579  ParsingDeclRAIIObject *TemplateDiags) {
2580  if (Tok.is(tok::at)) {
2581  if (getLangOpts().ObjC && NextToken().isObjCAtKeyword(tok::objc_defs))
2582  Diag(Tok, diag::err_at_defs_cxx);
2583  else
2584  Diag(Tok, diag::err_at_in_class);
2585 
2586  ConsumeToken();
2587  SkipUntil(tok::r_brace, StopAtSemi);
2588  return nullptr;
2589  }
2590 
2591  // Turn on colon protection early, while parsing declspec, although there is
2592  // nothing to protect there. It prevents from false errors if error recovery
2593  // incorrectly determines where the declspec ends, as in the example:
2594  // struct A { enum class B { C }; };
2595  // const int C = 4;
2596  // struct D { A::B : C; };
2597  ColonProtectionRAIIObject X(*this);
2598 
2599  // Access declarations.
2600  bool MalformedTypeSpec = false;
2601  if (!TemplateInfo.Kind &&
2602  Tok.isOneOf(tok::identifier, tok::coloncolon, tok::kw___super)) {
2603  if (TryAnnotateCXXScopeToken())
2604  MalformedTypeSpec = true;
2605 
2606  bool isAccessDecl;
2607  if (Tok.isNot(tok::annot_cxxscope))
2608  isAccessDecl = false;
2609  else if (NextToken().is(tok::identifier))
2610  isAccessDecl = GetLookAheadToken(2).is(tok::semi);
2611  else
2612  isAccessDecl = NextToken().is(tok::kw_operator);
2613 
2614  if (isAccessDecl) {
2615  // Collect the scope specifier token we annotated earlier.
2616  CXXScopeSpec SS;
2617  ParseOptionalCXXScopeSpecifier(SS, /*ObjectType=*/nullptr,
2618  /*ObjectHasErrors=*/false,
2619  /*EnteringContext=*/false);
2620 
2621  if (SS.isInvalid()) {
2622  SkipUntil(tok::semi);
2623  return nullptr;
2624  }
2625 
2626  // Try to parse an unqualified-id.
2627  SourceLocation TemplateKWLoc;
2628  UnqualifiedId Name;
2629  if (ParseUnqualifiedId(SS, /*ObjectType=*/nullptr,
2630  /*ObjectHadErrors=*/false, false, true, true,
2631  false, &TemplateKWLoc, Name)) {
2632  SkipUntil(tok::semi);
2633  return nullptr;
2634  }
2635 
2636  // TODO: recover from mistakenly-qualified operator declarations.
2637  if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::semi, diag::err_expected_after,
2638  "access declaration")) {
2639  SkipUntil(tok::semi);
2640  return nullptr;
2641  }
2642 
2643  // FIXME: We should do something with the 'template' keyword here.
2644  return DeclGroupPtrTy::make(DeclGroupRef(Actions.ActOnUsingDeclaration(
2645  getCurScope(), AS, /*UsingLoc*/ SourceLocation(),
2646  /*TypenameLoc*/ SourceLocation(), SS, Name,
2647  /*EllipsisLoc*/ SourceLocation(),
2648  /*AttrList*/ ParsedAttributesView())));
2649  }
2650  }
2651 
2652  // static_assert-declaration. A templated static_assert declaration is
2653  // diagnosed in Parser::ParseSingleDeclarationAfterTemplate.
2654  if (!TemplateInfo.Kind &&
2655  Tok.isOneOf(tok::kw_static_assert, tok::kw__Static_assert)) {
2656  SourceLocation DeclEnd;
2657  return DeclGroupPtrTy::make(
2658  DeclGroupRef(ParseStaticAssertDeclaration(DeclEnd)));
2659  }
2660 
2661  if (Tok.is(tok::kw_template)) {
2662  assert(!TemplateInfo.TemplateParams &&
2663  "Nested template improperly parsed?");
2664  ObjCDeclContextSwitch ObjCDC(*this);
2665  SourceLocation DeclEnd;
2666  return DeclGroupPtrTy::make(
2667  DeclGroupRef(ParseTemplateDeclarationOrSpecialization(
2668  DeclaratorContext::Member, DeclEnd, AccessAttrs, AS)));
2669  }
2670 
2671  // Handle: member-declaration ::= '__extension__' member-declaration
2672  if (Tok.is(tok::kw___extension__)) {
2673  // __extension__ silences extension warnings in the subexpression.
2674  ExtensionRAIIObject O(Diags); // Use RAII to do this.
2675  ConsumeToken();
2676  return ParseCXXClassMemberDeclaration(AS, AccessAttrs,
2677  TemplateInfo, TemplateDiags);
2678  }
2679 
2680  ParsedAttributes attrs(AttrFactory);
2681  ParsedAttributesView FnAttrs;
2682  // Optional C++11 attribute-specifier
2683  MaybeParseCXX11Attributes(attrs);
2684 
2685  // The next token may be an OpenMP pragma annotation token. That would
2686  // normally be handled from ParseCXXClassMemberDeclarationWithPragmas, but in
2687  // this case, it came from an *attribute* rather than a pragma. Handle it now.
2688  if (Tok.is(tok::annot_attr_openmp))
2689  return ParseOpenMPDeclarativeDirectiveWithExtDecl(AS, attrs);
2690 
2691  // We need to keep these attributes for future diagnostic
2692  // before they are taken over by declaration specifier.
2693  FnAttrs.addAll(attrs.begin(), attrs.end());
2694  FnAttrs.Range = attrs.Range;
2695 
2696  MaybeParseMicrosoftAttributes(attrs);
2697 
2698  if (Tok.is(tok::kw_using)) {
2699  // Eat 'using'.
2700  SourceLocation UsingLoc = ConsumeToken();
2701 
2702  // Consume unexpected 'template' keywords.
2703  while (Tok.is(tok::kw_template)) {
2704  SourceLocation TemplateLoc = ConsumeToken();
2705  Diag(TemplateLoc, diag::err_unexpected_template_after_using)
2706  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(TemplateLoc);
2707  }
2708 
2709  if (Tok.is(tok::kw_namespace)) {
2710  Diag(UsingLoc, diag::err_using_namespace_in_class);
2711  SkipUntil(tok::semi, StopBeforeMatch);
2712  return nullptr;
2713  }
2714  SourceLocation DeclEnd;
2715  // Otherwise, it must be a using-declaration or an alias-declaration.
2716  return ParseUsingDeclaration(DeclaratorContext::Member, TemplateInfo,
2717  UsingLoc, DeclEnd, attrs, AS);
2718  }
2719 
2720  // Hold late-parsed attributes so we can attach a Decl to them later.
2721  LateParsedAttrList CommonLateParsedAttrs;
2722 
2723  // decl-specifier-seq:
2724  // Parse the common declaration-specifiers piece.
2725  ParsingDeclSpec DS(*this, TemplateDiags);
2726  DS.takeAttributesFrom(attrs);
2727  if (MalformedTypeSpec)
2728  DS.SetTypeSpecError();
2729 
2730  // Turn off usual access checking for templates explicit specialization
2731  // and instantiation.
2732  // C++20 [temp.spec] 13.9/6.
2733  // This disables the access checking rules for member function template
2734  // explicit instantiation and explicit specialization.
2735  bool IsTemplateSpecOrInst =
2736  (TemplateInfo.Kind == ParsedTemplateInfo::ExplicitInstantiation ||
2737  TemplateInfo.Kind == ParsedTemplateInfo::ExplicitSpecialization);
2738  SuppressAccessChecks diagsFromTag(*this, IsTemplateSpecOrInst);
2739 
2740  ParseDeclarationSpecifiers(DS, TemplateInfo, AS, DeclSpecContext::DSC_class,
2741  &CommonLateParsedAttrs);
2742 
2743  if (IsTemplateSpecOrInst)
2744  diagsFromTag.done();
2745 
2746  // Turn off colon protection that was set for declspec.
2747  X.restore();
2748 
2749  // If we had a free-standing type definition with a missing semicolon, we
2750  // may get this far before the problem becomes obvious.
2751  if (DS.hasTagDefinition() &&
2752  TemplateInfo.Kind == ParsedTemplateInfo::NonTemplate &&
2753  DiagnoseMissingSemiAfterTagDefinition(DS, AS, DeclSpecContext::DSC_class,
2754  &CommonLateParsedAttrs))
2755  return nullptr;
2756 
2757  MultiTemplateParamsArg TemplateParams(
2758  TemplateInfo.TemplateParams? TemplateInfo.TemplateParams->data()
2759  : nullptr,
2760  TemplateInfo.TemplateParams? TemplateInfo.TemplateParams->size() : 0);
2761 
2762  if (TryConsumeToken(tok::semi)) {
2763  if (DS.isFriendSpecified())
2764  ProhibitAttributes(FnAttrs);
2765 
2766  RecordDecl *AnonRecord = nullptr;
2767  Decl *TheDecl = Actions.ParsedFreeStandingDeclSpec(
2768  getCurScope(), AS, DS, TemplateParams, false, AnonRecord);
2769  DS.complete(TheDecl);
2770  if (AnonRecord) {
2771  Decl* decls[] = {AnonRecord, TheDecl};
2772  return Actions.BuildDeclaratorGroup(decls);
2773  }
2774  return Actions.ConvertDeclToDeclGroup(TheDecl);
2775  }
2776 
2777  ParsingDeclarator DeclaratorInfo(*this, DS, DeclaratorContext::Member);
2778  if (TemplateInfo.TemplateParams)
2779  DeclaratorInfo.setTemplateParameterLists(TemplateParams);
2780  VirtSpecifiers VS;
2781 
2782  // Hold late-parsed attributes so we can attach a Decl to them later.
2783  LateParsedAttrList LateParsedAttrs;
2784 
2785  SourceLocation EqualLoc;
2786  SourceLocation PureSpecLoc;
2787 
2788  auto TryConsumePureSpecifier = [&] (bool AllowDefinition) {
2789  if (Tok.isNot(tok::equal))
2790  return false;
2791 
2792  auto &Zero = NextToken();
2793  SmallString<8> Buffer;
2794  if (Zero.isNot(tok::numeric_constant) ||
2795  PP.getSpelling(Zero, Buffer) != "0")
2796  return false;
2797 
2798  auto &After = GetLookAheadToken(2);
2799  if (!After.isOneOf(tok::semi, tok::comma) &&
2800  !(AllowDefinition &&
2801  After.isOneOf(tok::l_brace, tok::colon, tok::kw_try)))
2802  return false;
2803 
2804  EqualLoc = ConsumeToken();
2805  PureSpecLoc = ConsumeToken();
2806  return true;
2807  };
2808 
2809  SmallVector<Decl *, 8> DeclsInGroup;
2810  ExprResult BitfieldSize;
2811  ExprResult TrailingRequiresClause;
2812  bool ExpectSemi = true;
2813 
2814  // C++20 [temp.spec] 13.9/6.
2815  // This disables the access checking rules for member function template
2816  // explicit instantiation and explicit specialization.
2817  SuppressAccessChecks SAC(*this, IsTemplateSpecOrInst);
2818 
2819  // Parse the first declarator.
2820  if (ParseCXXMemberDeclaratorBeforeInitializer(
2821  DeclaratorInfo, VS, BitfieldSize, LateParsedAttrs)) {
2822  TryConsumeToken(tok::semi);
2823  return nullptr;
2824  }
2825 
2826  if (IsTemplateSpecOrInst)
2827  SAC.done();
2828 
2829  // Check for a member function definition.
2830  if (BitfieldSize.isUnset()) {
2831  // MSVC permits pure specifier on inline functions defined at class scope.
2832  // Hence check for =0 before checking for function definition.
2833  if (getLangOpts().MicrosoftExt && DeclaratorInfo.isDeclarationOfFunction())
2834  TryConsumePureSpecifier(/*AllowDefinition*/ true);
2835 
2836  FunctionDefinitionKind DefinitionKind = FunctionDefinitionKind::Declaration;
2837  // function-definition:
2838  //
2839  // In C++11, a non-function declarator followed by an open brace is a
2840  // braced-init-list for an in-class member initialization, not an
2841  // erroneous function definition.
2842  if (Tok.is(tok::l_brace) && !getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11) {
2843  DefinitionKind = FunctionDefinitionKind::Definition;
2844  } else if (DeclaratorInfo.isFunctionDeclarator()) {
2845  if (Tok.isOneOf(tok::l_brace, tok::colon, tok::kw_try)) {
2846  DefinitionKind = FunctionDefinitionKind::Definition;
2847  } else if (Tok.is(tok::equal)) {
2848  const Token &KW = NextToken();
2849  if (KW.is(tok::kw_default))
2850  DefinitionKind = FunctionDefinitionKind::Defaulted;
2851  else if (KW.is(tok::kw_delete))
2852  DefinitionKind = FunctionDefinitionKind::Deleted;
2853  else if (KW.is(tok::code_completion)) {
2854  cutOffParsing();
2855  Actions.CodeCompleteAfterFunctionEquals(DeclaratorInfo);
2856  return nullptr;
2857  }
2858  }
2859  }
2860  DeclaratorInfo.setFunctionDefinitionKind(DefinitionKind);
2861 
2862  // C++11 [dcl.attr.grammar] p4: If an attribute-specifier-seq appertains
2863  // to a friend declaration, that declaration shall be a definition.
2864  if (DeclaratorInfo.isFunctionDeclarator() &&
2865  DefinitionKind == FunctionDefinitionKind::Declaration &&
2866  DS.isFriendSpecified()) {
2867  // Diagnose attributes that appear before decl specifier:
2868  // [[]] friend int foo();
2869  ProhibitAttributes(FnAttrs);
2870  }
2871 
2872  if (DefinitionKind != FunctionDefinitionKind::Declaration) {
2873  if (!DeclaratorInfo.isFunctionDeclarator()) {
2874  Diag(DeclaratorInfo.getIdentifierLoc(), diag::err_func_def_no_params);
2875  ConsumeBrace();
2876  SkipUntil(tok::r_brace);
2877 
2878  // Consume the optional ';'
2879  TryConsumeToken(tok::semi);
2880 
2881  return nullptr;
2882  }
2883 
2884  if (DS.getStorageClassSpec() == DeclSpec::SCS_typedef) {
2885  Diag(DeclaratorInfo.getIdentifierLoc(),
2886  diag::err_function_declared_typedef);
2887 
2888  // Recover by treating the 'typedef' as spurious.
2889  DS.ClearStorageClassSpecs();
2890  }
2891 
2892  Decl *FunDecl =
2893  ParseCXXInlineMethodDef(AS, AccessAttrs, DeclaratorInfo, TemplateInfo,
2894  VS, PureSpecLoc);
2895 
2896  if (FunDecl) {
2897  for (unsigned i = 0, ni = CommonLateParsedAttrs.size(); i < ni; ++i) {
2898  CommonLateParsedAttrs[i]->addDecl(FunDecl);
2899  }
2900  for (unsigned i = 0, ni = LateParsedAttrs.size(); i < ni; ++i) {
2901  LateParsedAttrs[i]->addDecl(FunDecl);
2902  }
2903  }
2904  LateParsedAttrs.clear();
2905 
2906  // Consume the ';' - it's optional unless we have a delete or default
2907  if (Tok.is(tok::semi))
2908  ConsumeExtraSemi(AfterMemberFunctionDefinition);
2909 
2910  return DeclGroupPtrTy::make(DeclGroupRef(FunDecl));
2911  }
2912  }
2913 
2914  // member-declarator-list:
2915  // member-declarator
2916  // member-declarator-list ',' member-declarator
2917 
2918  while (true) {
2919  InClassInitStyle HasInClassInit = ICIS_NoInit;
2920  bool HasStaticInitializer = false;
2921  if (Tok.isOneOf(tok::equal, tok::l_brace) && PureSpecLoc.isInvalid()) {
2922  // DRXXXX: Anonymous bit-fields cannot have a brace-or-equal-initializer.
2923  if (BitfieldSize.isUsable() && !DeclaratorInfo.hasName()) {
2924  // Diagnose the error and pretend there is no in-class initializer.
2925  Diag(Tok, diag::err_anon_bitfield_member_init);
2926  SkipUntil(tok::comma, StopAtSemi | StopBeforeMatch);
2927  } else if (DeclaratorInfo.isDeclarationOfFunction()) {
2928  // It's a pure-specifier.

3106 /// ParseCXXMemberInitializer - Parse the brace-or-equal-initializer.
3107 /// Also detect and reject any attempted defaulted/deleted function definition.
3108 /// The location of the '=', if any, will be placed in EqualLoc.
3109 ///
3110 /// This does not check for a pure-specifier; that's handled elsewhere.
3111 ///
3112 /// brace-or-equal-initializer:
3113 /// '=' initializer-expression
3114 /// braced-init-list
3115 ///
3116 /// initializer-clause:
3117 /// assignment-expression
3118 /// braced-init-list
3119 ///
3120 /// defaulted/deleted function-definition:
3121 /// '=' 'default'
3122 /// '=' 'delete'
3123 ///
3124 /// Prior to C++0x, the assignment-expression in an initializer-clause must
3125 /// be a constant-expression.
3126 ExprResult Parser::ParseCXXMemberInitializer(Decl *D, bool IsFunction,
3127  SourceLocation &EqualLoc) {
3128  assert(Tok.isOneOf(tok::equal, tok::l_brace)
3129  && "Data member initializer not starting with '=' or '{'");
3130 
3131  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Context(
3132  Actions, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::PotentiallyEvaluated, D);
3133  if (TryConsumeToken(tok::equal, EqualLoc)) {
3134  if (Tok.is(tok::kw_delete)) {
3135  // In principle, an initializer of '= delete p;' is legal, but it will
3136  // never type-check. It's better to diagnose it as an ill-formed expression
3137  // than as an ill-formed deleted non-function member.
3138  // An initializer of '= delete p, foo' will never be parsed, because
3139  // a top-level comma always ends the initializer expression.
3140  const Token &Next = NextToken();
3141  if (IsFunction || Next.isOneOf(tok::semi, tok::comma, tok::eof)) {
3142  if (IsFunction)
3143  Diag(ConsumeToken(), diag::err_default_delete_in_multiple_declaration)
3144  << 1 /* delete */;
3145  else
3146  Diag(ConsumeToken(), diag::err_deleted_non_function);
3147  return ExprError();
3148  }
3149  } else if (Tok.is(tok::kw_default)) {
3150  if (IsFunction)
3151  Diag(Tok, diag::err_default_delete_in_multiple_declaration)
3152  << 0 /* default */;
3153  else
3154  Diag(ConsumeToken(), diag::err_default_special_members)
3155  << getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20;
3156  return ExprError();
3157  }
3158  }
3159  if (const auto *PD = dyn_cast_or_null<MSPropertyDecl>(D)) {
3160  Diag(Tok, diag::err_ms_property_initializer) << PD;
3161  return ExprError();
3162  }
3163  return ParseInitializer();
3164 }

3504 
3505  if (TagDecl)
3506  Actions.ActOnStartCXXMemberDeclarations(getCurScope(), TagDecl, FinalLoc,
3507  IsFinalSpelledSealed, IsAbstract,
3508  T.getOpenLocation());
3509 
3510  // C++ 11p3: Members of a class defined with the keyword class are private
3511  // by default. Members of a class defined with the keywords struct or union
3512  // are public by default.
3513  AccessSpecifier CurAS;
3514  if (TagType == DeclSpec::TST_class)
3515  CurAS = AS_private;
3516  else
3517  CurAS = AS_public;
3518  ParsedAttributes AccessAttrs(AttrFactory);
3519 
3520  if (TagDecl) {
3521  // While we still have something to read, read the member-declarations.
3522  while (!tryParseMisplacedModuleImport() && Tok.isNot(tok::r_brace) &&
3523  Tok.isNot(tok::eof)) {
3524  // Each iteration of this loop reads one member-declaration.
3525  ParseCXXClassMemberDeclarationWithPragmas(
3526  CurAS, AccessAttrs, static_cast<DeclSpec::TST>(TagType), TagDecl);
3527  MaybeDestroyTemplateIds();
3528  }
3529  T.consumeClose();
3530  } else {
3531  SkipUntil(tok::r_brace);
3532  }
3533 
3534  // If attributes exist after class contents, parse them.
3535  ParsedAttributes attrs(AttrFactory);
3536  MaybeParseGNUAttributes(attrs);
3537 
3538  if (TagDecl)
3539  Actions.ActOnFinishCXXMemberSpecification(getCurScope(), RecordLoc, TagDecl,
3540  T.getOpenLocation(),
3541  T.getCloseLocation(), attrs);
3542 
3543  // C++11 [class.mem]p2:
3544  // Within the class member-specification, the class is regarded as complete
3545  // within function bodies, default arguments, exception-specifications, and
3546  // brace-or-equal-initializers for non-static data members (including such
3547  // things in nested classes).
3548  if (TagDecl && NonNestedClass) {
3549  // We are not inside a nested class. This class and its nested classes
3550  // are complete and we can parse the delayed portions of method
3551  // declarations and the lexed inline method definitions, along with any
3552  // delayed attributes.
3553 
3554  SourceLocation SavedPrevTokLocation = PrevTokLocation;
3555  ParseLexedPragmas(getCurrentClass());
3556  ParseLexedAttributes(getCurrentClass());
3557  ParseLexedMethodDeclarations(getCurrentClass());
3558 
3559  // We've finished with all pending member declarations.
3560  Actions.ActOnFinishCXXMemberDecls();
3561 
3562  ParseLexedMemberInitializers(getCurrentClass());
3563  ParseLexedMethodDefs(getCurrentClass());
3564  PrevTokLocation = SavedPrevTokLocation;
3565 
3566  // We've finished parsing everything, including default argument
3567  // initializers.
3568  Actions.ActOnFinishCXXNonNestedClass();
3569  }
3570 
3571  if (TagDecl)
3572  Actions.ActOnTagFinishDefinition(getCurScope(), TagDecl, T.getRange());
3573 
3574  // Leave the class scope.
3575  ParsingDef.Pop();
3576  ClassScope.Exit();
3577 }

3600 /// ParseConstructorInitializer - Parse a C++ constructor initializer,
3601 /// which explicitly initializes the members or base classes of a
3602 /// class (C++ [class.base.init]). For example, the three initializers
3603 /// after the ':' in the Derived constructor below:
3604 ///
3605 /// @code
3606 /// class Base { };
3607 /// class Derived : Base {
3608 /// int x;
3609 /// float f;
3610 /// public:
3611 /// Derived(float f) : Base(), x(17), f(f) { }
3612 /// };
3613 /// @endcode
3614 ///
3615 /// [C++] ctor-initializer:
3616 /// ':' mem-initializer-list
3617 ///
3618 /// [C++] mem-initializer-list:
3619 /// mem-initializer ...[opt]
3620 /// mem-initializer ...[opt] , mem-initializer-list
3621 void Parser::ParseConstructorInitializer(Decl *ConstructorDecl) {
3622  assert(Tok.is(tok::colon) &&
3623  "Constructor initializer always starts with ':'");
3624 
3625  // Poison the SEH identifiers so they are flagged as illegal in constructor
3626  // initializers.
3627  PoisonSEHIdentifiersRAIIObject PoisonSEHIdentifiers(*this, true);
3628  SourceLocation ColonLoc = ConsumeToken();
3629 
3630  SmallVector<CXXCtorInitializer*, 4> MemInitializers;
3631  bool AnyErrors = false;
3632 
3633  do {
3634  if (Tok.is(tok::code_completion)) {
3635  cutOffParsing();
3636  Actions.CodeCompleteConstructorInitializer(ConstructorDecl,
3637  MemInitializers);
3638  return;
3639  }
3640 
3641  MemInitResult MemInit = ParseMemInitializer(ConstructorDecl);
3642  if (!MemInit.isInvalid())
3643  MemInitializers.push_back(MemInit.get());
3644  else
3645  AnyErrors = true;
3646 
3647  if (Tok.is(tok::comma))
3648  ConsumeToken();
3649  else if (Tok.is(tok::l_brace))
3650  break;
3651  // If the previous initializer was valid and the next token looks like a
3652  // base or member initializer, assume that we're just missing a comma.
3653  else if (!MemInit.isInvalid() &&
3654  Tok.isOneOf(tok::identifier, tok::coloncolon)) {
3655  SourceLocation Loc = PP.getLocForEndOfToken(PrevTokLocation);
3656  Diag(Loc, diag::err_ctor_init_missing_comma)
3657  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(Loc, ", ");
3658  } else {
3659  // Skip over garbage, until we get to '{'. Don't eat the '{'.
3660  if (!MemInit.isInvalid())
3661  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_expected_either) << tok::l_brace
3662  << tok::comma;
3663  SkipUntil(tok::l_brace, StopAtSemi | StopBeforeMatch);
3664  break;
3665  }
3666  } while (true);
3667 
3668  Actions.ActOnMemInitializers(ConstructorDecl, ColonLoc, MemInitializers,
3669  AnyErrors);
3670 }

3672 /// ParseMemInitializer - Parse a C++ member initializer, which is
3673 /// part of a constructor initializer that explicitly initializes one
3674 /// member or base class (C++ [class.base.init]). See
3675 /// ParseConstructorInitializer for an example.
3676 ///
3677 /// [C++] mem-initializer:
3678 /// mem-initializer-id '(' expression-list[opt] ')'
3679 /// [C++0x] mem-initializer-id braced-init-list
3680 ///
3681 /// [C++] mem-initializer-id:
3682 /// '::'[opt] nested-name-specifier[opt] class-name
3683 /// identifier
3684 MemInitResult Parser::ParseMemInitializer(Decl *ConstructorDecl) {
3685  // parse '::'[opt] nested-name-specifier[opt]
3686  CXXScopeSpec SS;
3687  if (ParseOptionalCXXScopeSpecifier(SS, /*ObjectType=*/nullptr,
3688  /*ObjectHasErrors=*/false,
3689  /*EnteringContext=*/false))
3690  return true;
3691 
3692  // : identifier
3693  IdentifierInfo *II = nullptr;
3694  SourceLocation IdLoc = Tok.getLocation();
3695  // : declype(...)
3696  DeclSpec DS(AttrFactory);
3697  // : template_name<...>
3698  TypeResult TemplateTypeTy;
3699 
3700  if (Tok.is(tok::identifier)) {
3701  // Get the identifier. This may be a member name or a class name,
3702  // but we'll let the semantic analysis determine which it is.
3703  II = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
3704  ConsumeToken();
3705  } else if (Tok.is(tok::annot_decltype)) {
3706  // Get the decltype expression, if there is one.
3707  // Uses of decltype will already have been converted to annot_decltype by
3708  // ParseOptionalCXXScopeSpecifier at this point.
3709  // FIXME: Can we get here with a scope specifier?
3710  ParseDecltypeSpecifier(DS);
3711  } else {
3712  TemplateIdAnnotation *TemplateId = Tok.is(tok::annot_template_id)
3713  ? takeTemplateIdAnnotation(Tok)
3714  : nullptr;
3715  if (TemplateId && TemplateId->mightBeType()) {
3716  AnnotateTemplateIdTokenAsType(SS, /*IsClassName*/true);
3717  assert(Tok.is(tok::annot_typename) && "template-id -> type failed");
3718  TemplateTypeTy = getTypeAnnotation(Tok);
3719  ConsumeAnnotationToken();
3720  } else {
3721  Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected_member_or_base_name);
3722  return true;
3723  }
3724  }
3725 
3726  // Parse the '('.
3727  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 && Tok.is(tok::l_brace)) {
3728  Diag(Tok, diag::warn_cxx98_compat_generalized_initializer_lists);
3729 
3730  // FIXME: Add support for signature help inside initializer lists.
3731  ExprResult InitList = ParseBraceInitializer();
3732  if (InitList.isInvalid())
3733  return true;
3734 
3735  SourceLocation EllipsisLoc;
3736  TryConsumeToken(tok::ellipsis, EllipsisLoc);
3737 
3738  if (TemplateTypeTy.isInvalid())
3739  return true;
3740  return Actions.ActOnMemInitializer(ConstructorDecl, getCurScope(), SS, II,
3741  TemplateTypeTy.get(), DS, IdLoc,
3742  InitList.get(), EllipsisLoc);
3743  } else if(Tok.is(tok::l_paren)) {
3744  BalancedDelimiterTracker T(*this, tok::l_paren);
3745  T.consumeOpen();
3746 
3747  // Parse the optional expression-list.
3748  ExprVector ArgExprs;
3749  CommaLocsTy CommaLocs;
3750  auto RunSignatureHelp = [&] {
3751  if (TemplateTypeTy.isInvalid())
3752  return QualType();
3753  QualType PreferredType = Actions.ProduceCtorInitMemberSignatureHelp(
3754  ConstructorDecl, SS, TemplateTypeTy.get(), ArgExprs, II,
3755  T.getOpenLocation(), /*Braced=*/false);
3756  CalledSignatureHelp = true;
3757  return PreferredType;
3758  };
3759  if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren) &&
3760  ParseExpressionList(ArgExprs, CommaLocs, [&] {
3761  PreferredType.enterFunctionArgument(Tok.getLocation(),
3762  RunSignatureHelp);
3763  })) {
3764  if (PP.isCodeCompletionReached() && !CalledSignatureHelp)
3765  RunSignatureHelp();
3766  SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
3767  return true;
3768  }
3769 
3770  T.consumeClose();
3771 
3772  SourceLocation EllipsisLoc;
3773  TryConsumeToken(tok::ellipsis, EllipsisLoc);
3774 
3775  if (TemplateTypeTy.isInvalid())
3776  return true;
3777  return Actions.ActOnMemInitializer(ConstructorDecl, getCurScope(), SS, II,
3778  TemplateTypeTy.get(), DS, IdLoc,
3779  T.getOpenLocation(), ArgExprs,
3780  T.getCloseLocation(), EllipsisLoc);
3781  }
3782 
3783  if (TemplateTypeTy.isInvalid())
3784  return true;
3785 
3786  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11)
3787  return Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected_either) << tok::l_paren << tok::l_brace;
3788  else
3789  return Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected) << tok::l_paren;
3790 }

3792 /// Parse a C++ exception-specification if present (C++0x [except.spec]).
3793 ///
3794 /// exception-specification:
3795 /// dynamic-exception-specification
3796 /// noexcept-specification
3797 ///
3798 /// noexcept-specification:
3799 /// 'noexcept'
3800 /// 'noexcept' '(' constant-expression ')'
3801 ExceptionSpecificationType
3802 Parser::tryParseExceptionSpecification(bool Delayed,
3803  SourceRange &SpecificationRange,
3804  SmallVectorImpl<ParsedType> &DynamicExceptions,
3805  SmallVectorImpl<SourceRange> &DynamicExceptionRanges,
3806  ExprResult &NoexceptExpr,
3807  CachedTokens *&ExceptionSpecTokens) {
3808  ExceptionSpecificationType Result = EST_None;
3809  ExceptionSpecTokens = nullptr;
3810 
3811  // Handle delayed parsing of exception-specifications.
3812  if (Delayed) {
3813  if (Tok.isNot(tok::kw_throw) && Tok.isNot(tok::kw_noexcept))
3814  return EST_None;
3815 
3816  // Consume and cache the starting token.
3817  bool IsNoexcept = Tok.is(tok::kw_noexcept);
3818  Token StartTok = Tok;
3819  SpecificationRange = SourceRange(ConsumeToken());
3820 
3821  // Check for a '('.
3822  if (!Tok.is(tok::l_paren)) {
3823  // If this is a bare 'noexcept', we're done.
3824  if (IsNoexcept) {
3825  Diag(Tok, diag::warn_cxx98_compat_noexcept_decl);
3826  NoexceptExpr = nullptr;
3827  return EST_BasicNoexcept;
3828  }
3829 
3830  Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected_lparen_after) << "throw";
3831  return EST_DynamicNone;
3832  }
3833 
3834  // Cache the tokens for the exception-specification.
3835  ExceptionSpecTokens = new CachedTokens;
3836  ExceptionSpecTokens->push_back(StartTok); // 'throw' or 'noexcept'
3837  ExceptionSpecTokens->push_back(Tok); // '('
3838  SpecificationRange.setEnd(ConsumeParen()); // '('
3839 
3840  ConsumeAndStoreUntil(tok::r_paren, *ExceptionSpecTokens,
3841  /*StopAtSemi=*/true,
3842  /*ConsumeFinalToken=*/true);
3843  SpecificationRange.setEnd(ExceptionSpecTokens->back().getLocation());
3844 
3845  return EST_Unparsed;
3846  }
3847 
3848  // See if there's a dynamic specification.
3849  if (Tok.is(tok::kw_throw)) {
3850  Result = ParseDynamicExceptionSpecification(SpecificationRange,
3851  DynamicExceptions,
3852  DynamicExceptionRanges);
3853  assert(DynamicExceptions.size() == DynamicExceptionRanges.size() &&
3854  "Produced different number of exception types and ranges.");
3855  }
3856 
3857  // If there's no noexcept specification, we're done.
3858  if (Tok.isNot(tok::kw_noexcept))
3859  return Result;
3860 
3861  Diag(Tok, diag::warn_cxx98_compat_noexcept_decl);
3862 
3863  // If we already had a dynamic specification, parse the noexcept for,
3864  // recovery, but emit a diagnostic and don't store the results.
3865  SourceRange NoexceptRange;
3866  ExceptionSpecificationType NoexceptType = EST_None;
3867 
3868  SourceLocation KeywordLoc = ConsumeToken();
3869  if (Tok.is(tok::l_paren)) {
3870  // There is an argument.
3871  BalancedDelimiterTracker T(*this, tok::l_paren);
3872  T.consumeOpen();
3873  NoexceptExpr = ParseConstantExpression();
3874  T.consumeClose();
3875  if (!NoexceptExpr.isInvalid()) {
3876  NoexceptExpr = Actions.ActOnNoexceptSpec(NoexceptExpr.get(),
3877  NoexceptType);
3878  NoexceptRange = SourceRange(KeywordLoc, T.getCloseLocation());
3879  } else {
3880  NoexceptType = EST_BasicNoexcept;
3881  }
3882  } else {
3883  // There is no argument.
3884  NoexceptType = EST_BasicNoexcept;
3885  NoexceptRange = SourceRange(KeywordLoc, KeywordLoc);
3886  }
3887 
3888  if (Result == EST_None) {
3889  SpecificationRange = NoexceptRange;
3890  Result = NoexceptType;
3891 
3892  // If there's a dynamic specification after a noexcept specification,
3893  // parse that and ignore the results.
3894  if (Tok.is(tok::kw_throw)) {
3895  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_dynamic_and_noexcept_specification);
3896  ParseDynamicExceptionSpecification(NoexceptRange, DynamicExceptions,
3897  DynamicExceptionRanges);
3898  }
3899  } else {
3900  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_dynamic_and_noexcept_specification);
3901  }
3902 
3903  return Result;
3904 }

3920 /// ParseDynamicExceptionSpecification - Parse a C++
3921 /// dynamic-exception-specification (C++ [except.spec]).
3922 ///
3923 /// dynamic-exception-specification:
3924 /// 'throw' '(' type-id-list [opt] ')'
3925 /// [MS] 'throw' '(' '...' ')'
3926 ///
3927 /// type-id-list:
3928 /// type-id ... [opt]
3929 /// type-id-list ',' type-id ... [opt]
3930 ///
3931 ExceptionSpecificationType Parser::ParseDynamicExceptionSpecification(
3932  SourceRange &SpecificationRange,
3933  SmallVectorImpl<ParsedType> &Exceptions,
3934  SmallVectorImpl<SourceRange> &Ranges) {
3935  assert(Tok.is(tok::kw_throw) && "expected throw");
3936 
3937  SpecificationRange.setBegin(ConsumeToken());
3938  BalancedDelimiterTracker T(*this, tok::l_paren);
3939  if (T.consumeOpen()) {
3940  Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected_lparen_after) << "throw";
3941  SpecificationRange.setEnd(SpecificationRange.getBegin());
3942  return EST_DynamicNone;
3943  }
3944 
3945  // Parse throw(...), a Microsoft extension that means "this function
3946  // can throw anything".
3947  if (Tok.is(tok::ellipsis)) {
3948  SourceLocation EllipsisLoc = ConsumeToken();
3949  if (!getLangOpts().MicrosoftExt)
3950  Diag(EllipsisLoc, diag::ext_ellipsis_exception_spec);
3951  T.consumeClose();
3952  SpecificationRange.setEnd(T.getCloseLocation());
3953  diagnoseDynamicExceptionSpecification(*this, SpecificationRange, false);
3954  return EST_MSAny;
3955  }
3956 
3957  // Parse the sequence of type-ids.
3958  SourceRange Range;
3959  while (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren)) {
3960  TypeResult Res(ParseTypeName(&Range));
3961 
3962  if (Tok.is(tok::ellipsis)) {
3963  // C++0x [temp.variadic]p5:
3964  // - In a dynamic-exception-specification (15.4); the pattern is a
3965  // type-id.
3966  SourceLocation Ellipsis = ConsumeToken();
3967  Range.setEnd(Ellipsis);
3968  if (!Res.isInvalid())
3969  Res = Actions.ActOnPackExpansion(Res.get(), Ellipsis);
3970  }
3971 
3972  if (!Res.isInvalid()) {
3973  Exceptions.push_back(Res.get());
3974  Ranges.push_back(Range);
3975  }
3976 
3977  if (!TryConsumeToken(tok::comma))
3978  break;
3979  }
3980 
3981  T.consumeClose();
3982  SpecificationRange.setEnd(T.getCloseLocation());
3983  diagnoseDynamicExceptionSpecification(*this, SpecificationRange,
3984  Exceptions.empty());
3985  return Exceptions.empty() ? EST_DynamicNone : EST_Dynamic;
3986 }

4001 /// Parse a requires-clause as part of a function declaration.
4002 void Parser::ParseTrailingRequiresClause(Declarator &D) {
4003  assert(Tok.is(tok::kw_requires) && "expected requires");
4004 
4005  SourceLocation RequiresKWLoc = ConsumeToken();
4006 
4007  ExprResult TrailingRequiresClause;
4008  ParseScope ParamScope(this,
4009  Scope::DeclScope |
4010  Scope::FunctionDeclarationScope |
4011  Scope::FunctionPrototypeScope);
4012 
4013  Actions.ActOnStartTrailingRequiresClause(getCurScope(), D);
4014 
4015  llvm::Optional<Sema::CXXThisScopeRAII> ThisScope;
4016  InitCXXThisScopeForDeclaratorIfRelevant(D, D.getDeclSpec(), ThisScope);
4017 
4018  TrailingRequiresClause =
4019  ParseConstraintLogicalOrExpression(/*IsTrailingRequiresClause=*/true);
4020 
4021  TrailingRequiresClause =
4022  Actions.ActOnFinishTrailingRequiresClause(TrailingRequiresClause);
4023 
4024  if (!D.isDeclarationOfFunction()) {
4025  Diag(RequiresKWLoc,
4026  diag::err_requires_clause_on_declarator_not_declaring_a_function);
4027  return;

4030  if (TrailingRequiresClause.isInvalid())
4031  SkipUntil({tok::l_brace, tok::arrow, tok::kw_try, tok::comma, tok::colon},
4032  StopAtSemi | StopBeforeMatch);
4033  else
4034  D.setTrailingRequiresClause(TrailingRequiresClause.get());
4035

4037  if (D.isFunctionDeclarator() && Tok.is(tok::arrow) &&

4039  SourceLocation ArrowLoc = Tok.getLocation();

4042  ParseTrailingReturnType(Range, /*MayBeFollowedByDirectInit=*/false);
4043

4046  diag::err_requires_clause_must_appear_after_trailing_return)
4047  << Range;

4049  FunctionChunk.HasTrailingReturnType = TrailingReturnType.isUsable();
4050  FunctionChunk.TrailingReturnType = TrailingReturnType.get();
4051  FunctionChunk.TrailingReturnTypeLoc = Range.getBegin();
4052  } else
4053  SkipUntil({tok::equal, tok::l_brace, tok::arrow, tok::kw_try, tok::comma},

4078 /// Pop the top class of the stack of classes that are
4079 /// currently being parsed.
4080 ///
4081 /// This routine should be called when we have finished parsing the
4082 /// definition of a class, but have not yet popped the Scope
4083 /// associated with the class's definition.
4084 void Parser::PopParsingClass(Sema::ParsingClassState state) {
4085  assert(!ClassStack.empty() && "Mismatched push/pop for class parsing");
4086 
4087  Actions.PopParsingClass(state);
4088 
4089  ParsingClass *Victim = ClassStack.top();
4090  ClassStack.pop();
4091  if (Victim->TopLevelClass) {
4092  // Deallocate all of the nested classes of this class,
4093  // recursively: we don't need to keep any of this information.
4094  DeallocateParsedClasses(Victim);
4095  return;
4096  }
4097  assert(!ClassStack.empty() && "Missing top-level class?");
4098 
4099  if (Victim->LateParsedDeclarations.empty()) {
4100  // The victim is a nested class, but we will not need to perform
4101  // any processing after the definition of this class since it has
4102  // no members whose handling was delayed. Therefore, we can just
4103  // remove this nested class.
4104  DeallocateParsedClasses(Victim);
4105  return;
4106  }

4108  // This nested class has some members that will need to be processed
4109  // after the top-level class is completely defined. Therefore, add
4110  // it to the list of nested classes within its parent.
4111  assert(getCurScope()->isClassScope() && "Nested class outside of class scope?");
4112  ClassStack.top()->LateParsedDeclarations.push_back(
4113  new LateParsedClass(this, Victim));
4114 }

4116 /// Try to parse an 'identifier' which appears within an attribute-token.
4117 ///
4118 /// \return the parsed identifier on success, and 0 if the next token is not an
4119 /// attribute-token.
4120 ///
4121 /// C++11 [dcl.attr.grammar]p3:
4122 /// If a keyword or an alternative token that satisfies the syntactic
4123 /// requirements of an identifier is contained in an attribute-token,
4124 /// it is considered an identifier.
4125 IdentifierInfo *
4126 Parser::TryParseCXX11AttributeIdentifier(SourceLocation &Loc,
4127  Sema::AttributeCompletion Completion,
4128  const IdentifierInfo *Scope) {
4129  switch (Tok.getKind()) {
4130  default:
4131  // Identifiers and keywords have identifier info attached.
4132  if (!Tok.isAnnotation()) {
4133  if (IdentifierInfo *II = Tok.getIdentifierInfo()) {
4134  Loc = ConsumeToken();
4135  return II;
4136  }
4137  }
4138  return nullptr;
4139 
4140  case tok::code_completion:
4141  cutOffParsing();
4142  Actions.CodeCompleteAttribute(getLangOpts().CPlusPlus ? ParsedAttr::AS_CXX11
4143  : ParsedAttr::AS_C2x,
4144  Completion, Scope);
4145  return nullptr;
4146 
4147  case tok::numeric_constant: {
4148  // If we got a numeric constant, check to see if it comes from a macro that
4149  // corresponds to the predefined __clang__ macro. If it does, warn the user
4150  // and recover by pretending they said _Clang instead.
4151  if (Tok.getLocation().isMacroID()) {
4152  SmallString<8> ExpansionBuf;
4153  SourceLocation ExpansionLoc =
4154  PP.getSourceManager().getExpansionLoc(Tok.getLocation());
4155  StringRef Spelling = PP.getSpelling(ExpansionLoc, ExpansionBuf);
4156  if (Spelling == "__clang__") {
4157  SourceRange TokRange(
4158  ExpansionLoc,
4159  PP.getSourceManager().getExpansionLoc(Tok.getEndLoc()));
4160  Diag(Tok, diag::warn_wrong_clang_attr_namespace)
4161  << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(TokRange, "_Clang");
4162  Loc = ConsumeToken();
4163  return &PP.getIdentifierTable().get("_Clang");
4164  }
4165  }
4166  return nullptr;
4167  }
4168 
4169  case tok::ampamp: // 'and'
4170  case tok::pipe: // 'bitor'
4171  case tok::pipepipe: // 'or'
4172  case tok::caret: // 'xor'
4173  case tok::tilde: // 'compl'
4174  case tok::amp: // 'bitand'
4175  case tok::ampequal: // 'and_eq'
4176  case tok::pipeequal: // 'or_eq'
4177  case tok::caretequal: // 'xor_eq'
4178  case tok::exclaim: // 'not'
4179  case tok::exclaimequal: // 'not_eq'
4180  // Alternative tokens do not have identifier info, but their spelling
4181  // starts with an alphabetical character.
4182  SmallString<8> SpellingBuf;
4183  SourceLocation SpellingLoc =
4184  PP.getSourceManager().getSpellingLoc(Tok.getLocation());
4185  StringRef Spelling = PP.getSpelling(SpellingLoc, SpellingBuf);
4186  if (isLetter(Spelling[0])) {
4187  Loc = ConsumeToken();
4188  return &PP.getIdentifierTable().get(Spelling);
4189  }
4190  return nullptr;
4191  }
4192 }
4193 
4194 void Parser::ParseOpenMPAttributeArgs(IdentifierInfo *AttrName,
4195  CachedTokens &OpenMPTokens) {
4196  // Both 'sequence' and 'directive' attributes require arguments, so parse the
4197  // open paren for the argument list.
4198  BalancedDelimiterTracker T(*this, tok::l_paren);
4199  if (T.consumeOpen()) {
4200  Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected) << tok::l_paren;
4201  return;
4202  }
4203 
4204  if (AttrName->isStr("directive")) {
4205  // If the attribute is named `directive`, we can consume its argument list
4206  // and push the tokens from it into the cached token stream for a new OpenMP
4207  // pragma directive.
4208  Token OMPBeginTok;
4209  OMPBeginTok.startToken();
4210  OMPBeginTok.setKind(tok::annot_attr_openmp);
4211  OMPBeginTok.setLocation(Tok.getLocation());
4212  OpenMPTokens.push_back(OMPBeginTok);
4213 
4214  ConsumeAndStoreUntil(tok::r_paren, OpenMPTokens, /*StopAtSemi=*/false,
4215  /*ConsumeFinalToken*/ false);
4216  Token OMPEndTok;
4217  OMPEndTok.startToken();
4218  OMPEndTok.setKind(tok::annot_pragma_openmp_end);
4219  OMPEndTok.setLocation(Tok.getLocation());
4220  OpenMPTokens.push_back(OMPEndTok);
4221  } else {
4222  assert(AttrName->isStr("sequence") &&
4223  "Expected either 'directive' or 'sequence'");
4224  // If the attribute is named 'sequence', its argument is a list of one or
4225  // more OpenMP attributes (either 'omp::directive' or 'omp::sequence',
4226  // where the 'omp::' is optional).
4227  do {
4228  // We expect to see one of the following:
4229  // * An identifier (omp) for the attribute namespace followed by ::
4230  // * An identifier (directive) or an identifier (sequence).
4231  SourceLocation IdentLoc;
4232  IdentifierInfo *Ident = TryParseCXX11AttributeIdentifier(IdentLoc);
4233 
4234  // If there is an identifier and it is 'omp', a double colon is required
4235  // followed by the actual identifier we're after.
4236  if (Ident && Ident->isStr("omp") && !ExpectAndConsume(tok::coloncolon))
4237  Ident = TryParseCXX11AttributeIdentifier(IdentLoc);
4238 
4239  // If we failed to find an identifier (scoped or otherwise), or we found
4240  // an unexpected identifier, diagnose.
4241  if (!Ident || (!Ident->isStr("directive") && !Ident->isStr("sequence"))) {
4242  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_expected_sequence_or_directive);
4243  SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopBeforeMatch);
4244  continue;
4245  }
4246  // We read an identifier. If the identifier is one of the ones we
4247  // expected, we can recurse to parse the args.
4248  ParseOpenMPAttributeArgs(Ident, OpenMPTokens);
4249 
4250  // There may be a comma to signal that we expect another directive in the
4251  // sequence.
4252  } while (TryConsumeToken(tok::comma));
4253  }
4254  // Parse the closing paren for the argument list.
4255  T.consumeClose();
4256 }

4258 static bool IsBuiltInOrStandardCXX11Attribute(IdentifierInfo *AttrName,
4259  IdentifierInfo *ScopeName) {
4260  switch (
4261  ParsedAttr::getParsedKind(AttrName, ScopeName, ParsedAttr::AS_CXX11)) {
4262  case ParsedAttr::AT_CarriesDependency:
4263  case ParsedAttr::AT_Deprecated:
4264  case ParsedAttr::AT_FallThrough:
4265  case ParsedAttr::AT_CXX11NoReturn:
4266  case ParsedAttr::AT_NoUniqueAddress:
4267  case ParsedAttr::AT_Likely:
4268  case ParsedAttr::AT_Unlikely:
4269  return true;
4270  case ParsedAttr::AT_WarnUnusedResult:
4271  return !ScopeName && AttrName->getName().equals("nodiscard");
4272  case ParsedAttr::AT_Unused:
4273  return !ScopeName && AttrName->getName().equals("maybe_unused");
4274  default:
4275  return false;
4276  }
4277 }

4279 /// ParseCXX11AttributeArgs -- Parse a C++11 attribute-argument-clause.
4280 ///
4281 /// [C++11] attribute-argument-clause:
4282 /// '(' balanced-token-seq ')'
4283 ///
4284 /// [C++11] balanced-token-seq:
4285 /// balanced-token
4286 /// balanced-token-seq balanced-token
4287 ///
4288 /// [C++11] balanced-token:
4289 /// '(' balanced-token-seq ')'
4290 /// '[' balanced-token-seq ']'
4291 /// '{' balanced-token-seq '}'
4292 /// any token but '(', ')', '[', ']', '{', or '}'
4293 bool Parser::ParseCXX11AttributeArgs(IdentifierInfo *AttrName,
4294  SourceLocation AttrNameLoc,
4295  ParsedAttributes &Attrs,
4296  SourceLocation *EndLoc,
4297  IdentifierInfo *ScopeName,
4298  SourceLocation ScopeLoc,
4299  CachedTokens &OpenMPTokens) {
4300  assert(Tok.is(tok::l_paren) && "Not a C++11 attribute argument list");
4301  SourceLocation LParenLoc = Tok.getLocation();
4302  const LangOptions &LO = getLangOpts();
4303  ParsedAttr::Syntax Syntax =
4304  LO.CPlusPlus ? ParsedAttr::AS_CXX11 : ParsedAttr::AS_C2x;
4305 
4306  // If the attribute isn't known, we will not attempt to parse any
4307  // arguments.
4308  if (!hasAttribute(LO.CPlusPlus ? AttrSyntax::CXX : AttrSyntax::C, ScopeName,
4309  AttrName, getTargetInfo(), getLangOpts())) {
4310  // Eat the left paren, then skip to the ending right paren.
4311  ConsumeParen();
4312  SkipUntil(tok::r_paren);
4313  return false;
4314  }
4315 
4316  if (ScopeName && (ScopeName->isStr("gnu") || ScopeName->isStr("__gnu__"))) {
4317  // GNU-scoped attributes have some special cases to handle GNU-specific
4318  // behaviors.
4319  ParseGNUAttributeArgs(AttrName, AttrNameLoc, Attrs, EndLoc, ScopeName,
4320  ScopeLoc, Syntax, nullptr);
4321  return true;
4322  }
4323 
4324  if (ScopeName && ScopeName->isStr("omp")) {
4325  Diag(AttrNameLoc, getLangOpts().OpenMP >= 51
4326  ? diag::warn_omp51_compat_attributes
4327  : diag::ext_omp_attributes);
4328 
4329  ParseOpenMPAttributeArgs(AttrName, OpenMPTokens);
4330 
4331  // We claim that an attribute was parsed and added so that one is not
4332  // created for us by the caller.
4333  return true;
4334  }
4335 
4336  unsigned NumArgs;
4337  // Some Clang-scoped attributes have some special parsing behavior.
4338  if (ScopeName && (ScopeName->isStr("clang") || ScopeName->isStr("_Clang")))
4339  NumArgs = ParseClangAttributeArgs(AttrName, AttrNameLoc, Attrs, EndLoc,
4340  ScopeName, ScopeLoc, Syntax);
4341  else
4342  NumArgs =
4343  ParseAttributeArgsCommon(AttrName, AttrNameLoc, Attrs, EndLoc,
4344  ScopeName, ScopeLoc, Syntax);
4345 
4346  if (!Attrs.empty() &&
4347  IsBuiltInOrStandardCXX11Attribute(AttrName, ScopeName)) {
4348  ParsedAttr &Attr = Attrs.back();
4349  // If the attribute is a standard or built-in attribute and we are
4350  // parsing an argument list, we need to determine whether this attribute
4351  // was allowed to have an argument list (such as [[deprecated]]), and how
4352  // many arguments were parsed (so we can diagnose on [[deprecated()]]).
4353  if (Attr.getMaxArgs() && !NumArgs) {
4354  // The attribute was allowed to have arguments, but none were provided
4355  // even though the attribute parsed successfully. This is an error.
4356  Diag(LParenLoc, diag::err_attribute_requires_arguments) << AttrName;
4357  Attr.setInvalid(true);
4358  } else if (!Attr.getMaxArgs()) {
4359  // The attribute parsed successfully, but was not allowed to have any
4360  // arguments. It doesn't matter whether any were provided -- the
4361  // presence of the argument list (even if empty) is diagnosed.
4362  Diag(LParenLoc, diag::err_cxx11_attribute_forbids_arguments)
4363  << AttrName
4364  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(SourceRange(LParenLoc, *EndLoc));
4365  Attr.setInvalid(true);
4366  }
4367  }
4368  return true;
4369 }

4371 /// Parse a C++11 or C2x attribute-specifier.
4372 ///
4373 /// [C++11] attribute-specifier:
4374 /// '[' '[' attribute-list ']' ']'
4375 /// alignment-specifier
4376 ///
4377 /// [C++11] attribute-list:
4378 /// attribute[opt]
4379 /// attribute-list ',' attribute[opt]
4380 /// attribute '...'
4381 /// attribute-list ',' attribute '...'
4382 ///
4383 /// [C++11] attribute:
4384 /// attribute-token attribute-argument-clause[opt]
4385 ///
4386 /// [C++11] attribute-token:
4387 /// identifier
4388 /// attribute-scoped-token
4389 ///
4390 /// [C++11] attribute-scoped-token:
4391 /// attribute-namespace '::' identifier
4392 ///
4393 /// [C++11] attribute-namespace:
4394 /// identifier
4395 void Parser::ParseCXX11AttributeSpecifierInternal(ParsedAttributes &Attrs,
4396  CachedTokens &OpenMPTokens,
4397  SourceLocation *EndLoc) {
4398  if (Tok.is(tok::kw_alignas)) {
4399  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_cxx98_compat_alignas);
4400  ParseAlignmentSpecifier(Attrs, EndLoc);
4401  return;
4402  }
4403 
4404  assert(Tok.is(tok::l_square) && NextToken().is(tok::l_square) &&
4405  "Not a double square bracket attribute list");
4406 
4407  SourceLocation OpenLoc = Tok.getLocation();
4408  Diag(OpenLoc, diag::warn_cxx98_compat_attribute);
4409 
4410  ConsumeBracket();
4411  checkCompoundToken(OpenLoc, tok::l_square, CompoundToken::AttrBegin);
4412  ConsumeBracket();
4413 
4414  SourceLocation CommonScopeLoc;
4415  IdentifierInfo *CommonScopeName = nullptr;
4416  if (Tok.is(tok::kw_using)) {
4417  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17
4418  ? diag::warn_cxx14_compat_using_attribute_ns
4419  : diag::ext_using_attribute_ns);
4420  ConsumeToken();
4421 
4422  CommonScopeName = TryParseCXX11AttributeIdentifier(
4423  CommonScopeLoc, Sema::AttributeCompletion::Scope);
4424  if (!CommonScopeName) {
4425  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_expected) << tok::identifier;
4426  SkipUntil(tok::r_square, tok::colon, StopBeforeMatch);
4427  }
4428  if (!TryConsumeToken(tok::colon) && CommonScopeName)
4429  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_expected) << tok::colon;
4430  }
4431 
4432  llvm::SmallDenseMap<IdentifierInfo*, SourceLocation, 4> SeenAttrs;
4433 
4434  bool AttrParsed = false;
4435  while (!Tok.isOneOf(tok::r_square, tok::semi, tok::eof)) {
4436  if (AttrParsed) {
4437  // If we parsed an attribute, a comma is required before parsing any
4438  // additional attributes.
4439  if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::comma)) {
4440  SkipUntil(tok::r_square, StopAtSemi | StopBeforeMatch);
4441  continue;
4442  }
4443  AttrParsed = false;
4444  }
4445 
4446  // Eat all remaining superfluous commas before parsing the next attribute.
4447  while (TryConsumeToken(tok::comma))
4448  ;
4449 
4450  SourceLocation ScopeLoc, AttrLoc;
4451  IdentifierInfo *ScopeName = nullptr, *AttrName = nullptr;
4452 
4453  AttrName = TryParseCXX11AttributeIdentifier(
4454  AttrLoc, Sema::AttributeCompletion::Attribute, CommonScopeName);
4455  if (!AttrName)
4456  // Break out to the "expected ']'" diagnostic.
4457  break;
4458 
4459  // scoped attribute
4460  if (TryConsumeToken(tok::coloncolon)) {
4461  ScopeName = AttrName;
4462  ScopeLoc = AttrLoc;
4463 
4464  AttrName = TryParseCXX11AttributeIdentifier(
4465  AttrLoc, Sema::AttributeCompletion::Attribute, ScopeName);
4466  if (!AttrName) {
4467  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_expected) << tok::identifier;
4468  SkipUntil(tok::r_square, tok::comma, StopAtSemi | StopBeforeMatch);
4469  continue;
4470  }
4471  }
4472 
4473  if (CommonScopeName) {
4474  if (ScopeName) {
4475  Diag(ScopeLoc, diag::err_using_attribute_ns_conflict)
4476  << SourceRange(CommonScopeLoc);
4477  } else {
4478  ScopeName = CommonScopeName;
4479  ScopeLoc = CommonScopeLoc;
4480  }
4481  }
4482 
4483  // Parse attribute arguments
4484  if (Tok.is(tok::l_paren))
4485  AttrParsed = ParseCXX11AttributeArgs(AttrName, AttrLoc, Attrs, EndLoc,
4486  ScopeName, ScopeLoc, OpenMPTokens);
4487 
4488  if (!AttrParsed) {
4489  Attrs.addNew(
4490  AttrName,
4491  SourceRange(ScopeLoc.isValid() ? ScopeLoc : AttrLoc, AttrLoc),
4492  ScopeName, ScopeLoc, nullptr, 0,
4493  getLangOpts().CPlusPlus ? ParsedAttr::AS_CXX11 : ParsedAttr::AS_C2x);
4494  AttrParsed = true;
4495  }
4496 
4497  if (TryConsumeToken(tok::ellipsis))
4498  Diag(Tok, diag::err_cxx11_attribute_forbids_ellipsis)
4499  << AttrName;
4500  }
4501 
4502  // If we hit an error and recovered by parsing up to a semicolon, eat the
4503  // semicolon and don't issue further diagnostics about missing brackets.
4504  if (Tok.is(tok::semi)) {
4505  ConsumeToken();
4506  return;
4507  }
4508 
4509  SourceLocation CloseLoc = Tok.getLocation();
4510  if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::r_square))
4511  SkipUntil(tok::r_square);
4512  else if (Tok.is(tok::r_square))
4513  checkCompoundToken(CloseLoc, tok::r_square, CompoundToken::AttrEnd);
4514  if (EndLoc)
4515  *EndLoc = Tok.getLocation();
4516  if (ExpectAndConsume(tok::r_square))
4517  SkipUntil(tok::r_square);
4518 }

4574 /// Parse uuid() attribute when it appears in a [] Microsoft attribute.
4575 void Parser::ParseMicrosoftUuidAttributeArgs(ParsedAttributes &Attrs) {
4576  assert(Tok.is(tok::identifier) && "Not a Microsoft attribute list");
4577  IdentifierInfo *UuidIdent = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
4578  assert(UuidIdent->getName() == "uuid" && "Not a Microsoft attribute list");
4579 
4580  SourceLocation UuidLoc = Tok.getLocation();
4581  ConsumeToken();
4582 
4583  // Ignore the left paren location for now.
4584  BalancedDelimiterTracker T(*this, tok::l_paren);
4585  if (T.consumeOpen()) {
4586  Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected) << tok::l_paren;
4587  return;
4588  }
4589 
4590  ArgsVector ArgExprs;
4591  if (Tok.is(tok::string_literal)) {
4592  // Easy case: uuid("...") -- quoted string.
4593  ExprResult StringResult = ParseStringLiteralExpression();
4594  if (StringResult.isInvalid())
4595  return;
4596  ArgExprs.push_back(StringResult.get());
4597  } else {
4598  // something like uuid({000000A0-0000-0000-C000-000000000049}) -- no
4599  // quotes in the parens. Just append the spelling of all tokens encountered
4600  // until the closing paren.
4601 
4602  SmallString<42> StrBuffer; // 2 "", 36 bytes UUID, 2 optional {}, 1 nul
4603  StrBuffer += "\"";
4604 
4605  // Since none of C++'s keywords match [a-f]+, accepting just tok::l_brace,
4606  // tok::r_brace, tok::minus, tok::identifier (think C000) and
4607  // tok::numeric_constant (0000) should be enough. But the spelling of the
4608  // uuid argument is checked later anyways, so there's no harm in accepting
4609  // almost anything here.
4610  // cl is very strict about whitespace in this form and errors out if any
4611  // is present, so check the space flags on the tokens.
4612  SourceLocation StartLoc = Tok.getLocation();
4613  while (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren)) {
4614  if (Tok.hasLeadingSpace() || Tok.isAtStartOfLine()) {
4615  Diag(Tok, diag::err_attribute_uuid_malformed_guid);
4616  SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
4617  return;
4618  }
4619  SmallString<16> SpellingBuffer;
4620  SpellingBuffer.resize(Tok.getLength() + 1);
4621  bool Invalid = false;
4622  StringRef TokSpelling = PP.getSpelling(Tok, SpellingBuffer, &Invalid);
4623  if (Invalid) {
4624  SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
4625  return;
4626  }
4627  StrBuffer += TokSpelling;
4628  ConsumeAnyToken();
4629  }
4630  StrBuffer += "\"";
4631 
4632  if (Tok.hasLeadingSpace() || Tok.isAtStartOfLine()) {
4633  Diag(Tok, diag::err_attribute_uuid_malformed_guid);
4634  ConsumeParen();
4635  return;
4636  }
4637 
4638  // Pretend the user wrote the appropriate string literal here.
4639  // ActOnStringLiteral() copies the string data into the literal, so it's
4640  // ok that the Token points to StrBuffer.
4641  Token Toks[1];
4642  Toks[0].startToken();
4643  Toks[0].setKind(tok::string_literal);
4644  Toks[0].setLocation(StartLoc);
4645  Toks[0].setLiteralData(StrBuffer.data());
4646  Toks[0].setLength(StrBuffer.size());
4647  StringLiteral *UuidString =
4648  cast<StringLiteral>(Actions.ActOnStringLiteral(Toks, nullptr).get());
4649  ArgExprs.push_back(UuidString);
4650  }
4651 
4652  if (!T.consumeClose()) {
4653  Attrs.addNew(UuidIdent, SourceRange(UuidLoc, T.getCloseLocation()), nullptr,
4654  SourceLocation(), ArgExprs.data(), ArgExprs.size(),
4655  ParsedAttr::AS_Microsoft);
4656  }
4657 }
4658 
4659 /// ParseMicrosoftAttributes - Parse Microsoft attributes [Attr]
4660 ///
4661 /// [MS] ms-attribute:
4662 /// '[' token-seq ']'
4663 ///
4664 /// [MS] ms-attribute-seq:
4665 /// ms-attribute[opt]
4666 /// ms-attribute ms-attribute-seq
4667 void Parser::ParseMicrosoftAttributes(ParsedAttributes &Attrs) {
4668  assert(Tok.is(tok::l_square) && "Not a Microsoft attribute list");
4669 
4670  SourceLocation StartLoc = Tok.getLocation();
4671  SourceLocation EndLoc = StartLoc;
4672  do {
4673  // FIXME: If this is actually a C++11 attribute, parse it as one.
4674  BalancedDelimiterTracker T(*this, tok::l_square);
4675  T.consumeOpen();
4676 
4677  // Skip most ms attributes except for a specific list.
4678  while (true) {
4679  SkipUntil(tok::r_square, tok::identifier,
4680  StopAtSemi | StopBeforeMatch | StopAtCodeCompletion);
4681  if (Tok.is(tok::code_completion)) {
4682  cutOffParsing();
4683  Actions.CodeCompleteAttribute(AttributeCommonInfo::AS_Microsoft,
4684  Sema::AttributeCompletion::Attribute,
4685  /*Scope=*/nullptr);
4686  break;
4687  }
4688  if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) // ']', but also eof
4689  break;
4690  if (Tok.getIdentifierInfo()->getName() == "uuid")
4691  ParseMicrosoftUuidAttributeArgs(Attrs);
4692  else
4693  ConsumeToken();
4694  }
4695 
4696  T.consumeClose();
4697  EndLoc = T.getCloseLocation();
4698  } while (Tok.is(tok::l_square));
4699 
4700  Attrs.Range = SourceRange(StartLoc, EndLoc);
4701 }
4702 
4703 void Parser::ParseMicrosoftIfExistsClassDeclaration(
4704  DeclSpec::TST TagType, ParsedAttributes &AccessAttrs,
4705  AccessSpecifier &CurAS) {
4706  IfExistsCondition Result;
4707  if (ParseMicrosoftIfExistsCondition(Result))
4708  return;
4709 
4710  BalancedDelimiterTracker Braces(*this, tok::l_brace);
4711  if (Braces.consumeOpen()) {
4712  Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected) << tok::l_brace;
4713  return;
4714  }
4715 
4716  switch (Result.Behavior) {
4717  case IEB_Parse:
4718  // Parse the declarations below.
4719  break;
4720 
4721  case IEB_Dependent:
4722  Diag(Result.KeywordLoc, diag::warn_microsoft_dependent_exists)
4723  << Result.IsIfExists;
4724  // Fall through to skip.
4725  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4726 
4727  case IEB_Skip:
4728  Braces.skipToEnd();
4729  return;
4730  }
4731 
4732  while (Tok.isNot(tok::r_brace) && !isEofOrEom()) {
4733  // __if_exists, __if_not_exists can nest.
4734  if (Tok.isOneOf(tok::kw___if_exists, tok::kw___if_not_exists)) {
4735  ParseMicrosoftIfExistsClassDeclaration(TagType,
4736  AccessAttrs, CurAS);
4737  continue;
4738  }
4739 
4740  // Check for extraneous top-level semicolon.
4741  if (Tok.is(tok::semi)) {
4742  ConsumeExtraSemi(InsideStruct, TagType);
4743  continue;
4744  }
4745 
4746  AccessSpecifier AS = getAccessSpecifierIfPresent();
4747  if (AS != AS_none) {
4748  // Current token is a C++ access specifier.
4749  CurAS = AS;
4750  SourceLocation ASLoc = Tok.getLocation();
4751  ConsumeToken();
4752  if (Tok.is(tok::colon))
4753  Actions.ActOnAccessSpecifier(AS, ASLoc, Tok.getLocation(),
4754  ParsedAttributesView{});
4755  else
4756  Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected) << tok::colon;
4757  ConsumeToken();
4758  continue;
4759  }
4760 
4761  // Parse all the comma separated declarators.
4762  ParseCXXClassMemberDeclaration(CurAS, AccessAttrs);
4763  }
4764 
4765  Braces.consumeClose();
4766 }
